title: baked corn
directions: Add slightly beaten eggs, salt, butter and milk to corn.
Turn into a buttered baking dish.
Bake in a moderate oven until firm (about 45 minutes).

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In crock-pot on low, add sausage, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese.
Stir occasionally until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oven easy chicken
directions: In a small bowl, mix together dressing, soup mix, preserves and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.
Sauce is delicious served over rice.

title: turkey chili
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick coating.
Cook turkey and celery until turkey is no longer pink, stirring to break up pieces.
Stir in undrained tomatoes and remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup water. Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
May add a little more water.
Discard bay leaf.
Ladle into bowls.
Low fat and really tastes good.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add flour mixture and milk, alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Grease
muffin pan; fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix
dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat
remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch
pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and
egg
until
light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle
with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer. Cut
into
bars.
If
more
lemon
flavor
is
desired, add 3/4 teaspoon lemon flavoring with lemon juice.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients except cornflakes and cheese.
Let stand 1 hour.
Spoon into buttered oblong 2-quart dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes and cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour in well buttered casserole.
Add topping and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Spray a cookie sheet with Pam. In a large bowl, add in this order oats, sesame seed, coconut, wheat germ and sunflower seeds. Mix thoroughly and add oil, honey and molasses and stir. Spread evenly on cookie sheet. Place in oven and cook until golden brown. Stir frequently (about one hour). Add your choice of any or all of the following:
chopped pecans, sliced almonds, dried fruit bits, raisins, dried cranberries and apricots. Stir and return to oven briefly. Cool completely and store in airtight containers. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello into boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Measure this liquid and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add to jello mixture.
Stir in drained berries and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart flat dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In 9 x 7-inch dish, mix sweet potatoes, vanilla, 2 eggs, milk, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup margarine.
Make topping with brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1/3 cup margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, frozen lemonade and Eagle Brand milk with a mixer.
Pour into pie crust and chill in refrigerator until solid, about 2 to 3 hours.

title: charcoal-grilled salmon steak
directions: Thaw steaks if frozen and put in well-greased hinged wire grills.
Mix remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Baste fish with the mixture and sprinkle with paprika.

title: souper joes
directions: Cook hamburger; drain. Add rest of the ingredients. Heat and put on buns.

title: chicken casserole with stuffing and peas
directions: Mix milk, soup, peas, chicken, rice and cheese; set aside.
In separate bowl mix stuffing, French onions, butter, and seasoning pack for stuffing.
Pour chicken mixture into baking dish.
Put stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef in wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle meat lightly with garlic powder.
Put in heavy casserole or Dutch oven.
Pour sherry over meat and let marinate for 1 to 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients (except carrots) and pour over meat.
Mix well.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Add carrots the last 15 minutes of cooking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: angel food cake delight
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Prepare Jell-O as directed.
Let set until firm but not stiff.
Whip Jell-O; add drained fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in bite size cake.
Pour in a dish; let chill.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and syrup; bring to a boil.
Cook until soft ball forms when dropped into cold water.
Add peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish and allow to cool.

title: crab mousse
directions: Mix
cream
cheese
and onion.	Heat
until
warm.
Add soup, bring to boil, stirring
constantly.
Take	package
of Knox gelatine and
dissolve in water.
Add to hot cream cheese and soup. Add crabmeat, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Add 3 to 6 drops of	red
food
coloring.
Pour into oiled mold and let set.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Roll bread in melted margarine, then in Parmesan cheese. Place on cookie sheet or in Tupperware container with wax paper between layers.
Store in refrigerator until needed (1 hour or longer).
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Simmer onion in oil and butter until golden.
Add paprika and blend.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and seasoned chicken stock to onion mixture.
When boiling point is reached, add chicken.
Simmer covered until tender, about 1 hour.
In separate bowl, mix together flour and sour cream.
Stir slowly into pot.
Heat with chicken 5 minutes (do not boil).
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and baking powder (sifted twice) alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and pinch of salt.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Put shredded cabbage in kettle and add boiling water.
Cook, covered, 10 minutes.
Add apples and cook 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Add additional vinegar or brown sugar, depending on personal taste. We leave recipe as is.
Serve with pork chops, bratwurst or potato pancakes.

title: three thing pie
directions: Melt candy bar in double boiler.
Fold in Cool Whip, stirring well.
Put in pie crust.
Chill 1 hour or longer.

title: cucumber salad ii
directions: Proceed as for Cucumber Salad I, but omit olive oil and sugar and substitute sour cream and dill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Pour these ingredients over cooked mostaccioli and mix.
Add to this:

title: bobby g's clam chowder
directions: Place the bacon in an 8-quart pot with a heavy bottom.
Cook over medium heat until just browned; pour off the grease.
Add the onions, celery, carrots and butter to the bacon; saute until the vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate sweet potatoes.
Add milk immediately to avoid potatoes from discoloring.
Add sugar, eggs and melted butter.
Add ginger and dash of salt.
Cook in baking dish at 350°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in flour sifter and sift into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Make three holes in mixture.
Spoon evenly, in first hole the vinegar; the second whole the vanilla; and the butter in the third hole.
Pour the cold water over entire thing and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Simmer onions and peppers in water for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over 3 pieces of cut up toast.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Good with beef.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: In mixing bowl combine pudding mix and milk until thick.
Mix in condensed milk and cool whip.
Beat well.
In large bowl, layer vanilla wafers, pudding mixture then bananas.
Continue to layer leaving wafers on very top.
Chill at least for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Stir before serving.
Serve with your favorite dippers or crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: banana brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell for 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 325°.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Drain all of the beans and save the liquid.
Brown bacon, beef and onion.
Add all of the drained beans and mix well. Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, ketchup, melted shortening, salt, vinegar and enough of bean liquid to just cover the mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
If mixture appears dry, more bean liquid may be added.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets and cut tops, about 2-inches from beet.
Cook beets until tender.
Set aside to cool.
When cool enough to handle, peel beets and cut in slices or chunks whichever you prefer.
Mix sugar, vinegar, water and pickling spices and bring to a boil. Add beets and boil 1 minute.
Put in jars and seal.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Steam vegetables until tender; drain.
Arrange in 3-quart casserole which has been buttered.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked ham and corn casserole
directions: Brown ham, onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add flour; stir well.
Add milk all at once; stir until mixture thickens and boils.

title: chicken in gravy
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, celery salt, garlic powder and bouillon cubes together in bowl.
Dip chicken in this mixture and fry in large deep pot in grease.
When chicken is all cooked, pour off all grease except a little.
Put leftover flour in grease or 3 tablespoons flour to thicken.
Add large glass of water.
Put chicken back in gravy and turn down and cook 1 hour.
Put lid on this.

title: crock pot corn
directions: Mix together in crock-pot. Heat until ready to serve.

title: caramel chocolate chip bars
directions: Take 1/2 mix and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan (lightly buttered).
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread caramel mixture evenly over the top.
Sprinkle a 12 ounce package of chocolate chips over the top while still warm. Pour last 1/2 of cake mix over top of this and spread it.
Bake another 12 minutes or longer until done.
Cool in fridge 30 minutes prior to serving.

title: charleston orange balls
directions: Mix all.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in more 4x sugar.
Store in tin box.
If keeping longer than a week, put in refrigerator, will stay fresh indefinitely.
Makes about 60.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine with cornmeal and mix thoroughly.
In separate bowl, mix egg, oil and milk.
Add dry ingredients and mix well with large spoon, but do not beat.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full or pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in
greased	baking	pan
or iron frying pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli as directed and drain. Chop onion and saute in butter.
Beat eggs and add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: pepsi salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add enough boiling water to juice to make 1 cup.
Dissolve jello in juice.
Cool; add pineapple, cream cheese, nuts and last of all, Pepsi.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: breakfast pancakes
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Melt butter.
Add melted butter, egg and milk to flour mixture. Cook in greased griddle.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Crumble flour, sugar and butter together as for pie dough. Beat 2 eggs in cup, then fill to top with milk.
Add baking powder and vanilla to egg mixture.
Wash berries; let drain, then lightly flour berries.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Use cupcake liners for easier removal from muffin tins.

title: "jan's" quick navy bean soup
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Add garlic and stir for one minute. Add ham; saute on low to medium heat for a few minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Heat on medium for 5 minutes; reduce to simmer.
Serve when hot.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: jello cake
directions: Chill Milnot overnight.
Prepare jello, 1 cup hot water in a separate bowl for each color/flavor.
Mix each bowl well.
Let cool.
Mix 1 can Milnot with 2 teaspoons vanilla, beat until very fluffy (10 minutes); place in fridge.
Follow same directions for second can of Milnot.
Place equal amount of Milnot into jello and fold.
Spoon into large bowl creatively.
Chill at least 4 to 6 hours.
Enjoy.
Decorate with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: strawberry ice cream soda
directions: In large glass combine milk and strawberry drink mix until blended.
Add seltzer.
Top with a scoop of frozen yogurt.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread the broccoli on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top that with the cut up chicken.
Cover the chicken with the soup mixture.
Sprinkle the cheese over the top and sprinkle some bread crumbs over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Lay pork chops on top of mixture.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix cool broth, shortening, salt, pepper and eggs.
Add flour until it feels like biscuit dough.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick; cut in pillars and drop in broth.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in 3 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar; add nuts, bananas, flour and soda. Put in a greased pan lined with wax paper.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour half in the bottom of a hot greased pan.
Add cheese and peppers, then pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 375 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in container with lid.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour, preferably longer, before serving.
The longer it's refrigerated, the better it tastes.

title: chiffon pie
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and juice until it begins to thicken.
Add jello; cook for 3 minutes.
Chill until it begins to thicken. Whip the Carnation milk very stiff; fold into mixture.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: dressed up green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Boil rapidly until liquid has boiled down, then cook slowly for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Remove bones and skin from chicken and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together broth, soup, mixed vegetables, salt and pepper. Pour this mixture over chicken.
Mix together flour,
milk and butter or margarine.
Pour this over the mixed vegetable mixture. Cook at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: gail's old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, vegetable oil and both sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Roll teaspoon of soft dough into a ball. Roll ball in granulated sugar.
Press down lightly on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 8 dozen.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, sugar, cocoa, nuts and cornstarch. Add rum, them make into balls.

title: lemon pillow cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box. Put in 9 x 13 dish. Drop blobs of lemon pie filling on top. Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes. Check for doneness.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils as directed on package.
Place in kettle and cover with ample water; let stand overnight.
Drain and discard the soaking water.
Place lentils, ham hock, carrot, celery and onion in crock-pot
Cover lentils and ham hock with water and add the bouillon cubes or instant broth.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sausage, bay leaf and spices to taste.
Cover and cook in crock-pot approximately 3 to 4 hours.
When soup is almost ready, remove ham hock and cut into small pieces.
Return pieces to soup.

title: mother's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, shortening and both sugars.
Add flour, sifted with cream of tartar and soda.
Add vanilla last.
Roll in small balls and flatten with glass.
Sprinkle with sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
(I sometimes roll mine; wrap and put in freezer until firm and then slice into cookies.)
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Grease and flour bundt pan. Mix the first 6 ingredients together. Fold the chocolate chips into the batter. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: geraldine och's german pfeffernuesse(pepper nuts)
directions: Boil molasses; let cool.
Melt butter and lard together; let cool.
Add sugar to melted butter mixture, then add eggs, molasses and rest of ingredients, except flour.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time.
Dough will be very stiff.
Roll into 1/2-inch rolls (about thickness of forefinger).
Cut into pieces as wide as they are thick.
Bake a sample (bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until cookies are lightly browned on bottom and cooked clear through).

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: In a bowl, mix sour cream and soup, then add potatoes.
Add 1/2 of cheese and mix thoroughly.
Put mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and pour butter over potatoes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage with ingredients. Chill until ready to serve.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Mix egg and sugar well, then add vinegar and bring to a boil. Next, add butter and let cool.
This can be used for potato salad or other salads that require dressing.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Separate crescent rolls and spread in 12 x 18-inch greased pan.
Bake 12 minutes.
Blend next seven items and spread it over cooled crust.
Add your choice of vegetables and top with shredded cheese.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Mix flour, garlic, salt or powder and paprika.
Coat chicken with mixture.
Brown chicken in butter in skillet.
Remove chicken; stir in water, lemon juice and bouillon cube.
Crush cube and stir it up, loosening particles stuck to pan.
Add lemon slices.
Return chicken to pan.
Heat and serve.
Pour broth onto chicken.

title: coconut cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened
condensed milk until smooth.
On low speed, beat in water
and
pudding mix until smooth. Fold in whipped cream and coconut.
Pour
into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana bread
directions: Into a large mixing bowl, sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix in raisins and nuts.
Add margarine and sugar and beat until fluffy; add eggs, vanilla and bananas and mix well. Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: classic french dressing
directions: When making the dressing at the dinner table: Pour olive oil over greens and toss until greens are coated. Add vinegar, salt and pepper and toss well. When making the dressing in advance, simply combine all the ingredients in a jar or cruet. Cover. Shake well before using.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cabbage and tomato soup in a large mixing bowl.
Place cabbage heads in hot water to make leaves wet and easier to handle.
Separate cabbage leaves and roll mixture up in leaves.
Place in baking dish.
Pour tomato soup over top.
Cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cake will crack open on top.

title: eight layer casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef until brown. Drain off fat. Stir in tomato sauce, basil, sugar, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Combine sour cream, cream cheese, milk and onion. In a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 of the noodles, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 of the cream cheese mixture, then all the spinach. Layer with remaining noodles and meat. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Chill remaining cream cheese mixture. After 45 minutes, spread remaining cream cheese mixture and top with shredded cheese. Bake, uncovered, an additional 10 minutes. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: peggy's punch
directions: Dissolve jello (any flavor) in 9 cups water.
Combine 4 cups sugar in 4 cups water; bring to a boil.
Add jello mixture and cool.
When cool, add 16 ounces lemon juice and 2 cans pineapple juice.
Mix well and freeze.
Before serving, add 2 bottles of ginger ale or 7-Up.
Serves 40 to 50 people.

title: rustic lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions, but do not add salt.

title: westerner cake
directions: Leave out eggs and oleo at room temperature.
Cream the oleo; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour gradually to batter.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Bake in a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool 4 minutes.
Invert.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and peanut butter.
Microwave on High setting for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add marshmallow cream and nuts, stirring well.
Pour into pan and cool.
Slice and enjoy.

title: inside-out ravioli
directions: Cook shells al dente and drain.
In the meantime, cook spinach according to package directions.
Combine spinach, cheeses, eggs, oil and bread crumbs.
Combine this mixture with shells; layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and cover with favorite meat sauce. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple in lightly buttered 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with cake mix, blueberries and sugar. Drizzle with butter. Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; add butter to hot rice to melt, then add mushrooms, soup and corn.
Pour into buttered dish and top with cheese slices.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Bake or broil chicken until done.
Put broth in saucepan.
Turn on high (stir often to keep from sticking).
Take one biscuit at a time and tear in bite sizes.
Put in chicken broth.
Stir after two biscuits.
You may not need but 15 biscuits.
It depends on how thick you want the dumplings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well with electric mixer; cook 45 minutes at 350°. Let set for 1 hour.

title: cream pear salad
directions: Refrigerate for 4 hours.
DO NOT STIR!

title: hot or cold vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add beef, stirring until brown.
Add onions and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a bean pot or 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a hot oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Butter loaf pan 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Combine sugar, milk, cocoa, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cocoa is melted and sugar dissolved. Let boil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Let cool for a few minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat vigorously and continuously 5 to 10 minutes with wooden spoon until candy is thick and no longer glossy.
Quickly stir in nuts.
Spread mixture in buttered pan.
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: pear relish
directions: Cook 15 minutes.
Grind peppers and onions.
Do not drain.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 4 cake pans. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cola chicken
directions: Place chicken in skillet. Mix ketchup and Coke.
Pour over chicken. Add green pepper, onion and mushrooms (sliced or chopped). Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well. Sift flour, soda and spices together.
Add to butter and sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add jam last, beating only enough to mix well.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart and with a fork dipped in flour, flatten ball with a crisscross pattern.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.

title: cauliflower and ham chowder(a good soup)
directions: In a large covered saucepan, cook celery and cauliflower in chicken broth until almost tender, about 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
In mixing bowl, gradually stir in half and half or evaporated milk into potato soup.
Blend water, cornstarch and pepper.
Stir in ham.
Simmer on low 10 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in cheese.

title: greek melama karona
directions: Combine and beat oil and butter until blended.
Beat in 1/3 cup sugar and add 1 tablespoon orange juice, baking powder and soda.
Mix well.
With mixer, add enough flour (a little at a time) to make a soft dough.
Shape dough into 2-inch ovals and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes or until lightly golden.
Cool on wire rack.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix Monterey Jack cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, onion, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper; reserve.
Heat tomato sauce, water, green pepper, chili powder, oregano, cumin and garlic to boiling, stirring occasionally; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Pour into ungreased pie plate, 8 or 9 x 1 1/4-inches.

title: sauce (holiday beef rib-eye roast)
directions: Combine sauce ingredients.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until bubbly, stirring occasionally.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and spices; set aside.
In separate bowl, combine sour milk (lemon juice should make the milk curdle), mashed bananas and nuts; set aside.
Now cream together the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and sour milk mixture to the creamed mixture; mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy pineapple casserole
directions: Crush crackers in plastic bag.
With crackers on bottom, bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: italian beef
directions: Put in a crock-pot and cook either all day or night on high.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients in large covered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until done.
Stir in 1/2 to 1 cup sour cream before serving.

title: layered ranchero dip
directions: On a 15 x 10-inch or large shallow serving platter, thinly spread bean dip.
In a small bowl combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread over bean dip.
Peel, pit and mash avocados.
Combine with lime juice, salt and garlic powder. Spread this over the mayonnaise and seasoning layer. Sprinkle cheese, olives, tomatoes and onions over last layer.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Butter 6 x 10 casserole.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole.	Crush crackers and spread on top.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Sprinkle little Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: jalapeno chili salsa
directions: Puree all together in blender.

title: bean and cornbread casserole
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high
heat
until hot.
Add onions, 1/2 cup green pepper and
garlic;
cook, stirring constantly, until tender. Stir in kidney beans and next 7 ingredients.
Cover and cook 5 minutes; pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.

title: cranberry raisin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add raisins; stir in egg, cranberry sauce and oil.
Add dry ingredients to cranberry mixture.
Stir.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° about 45 minutes until browned.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for a few hours and serve with your favorite fruits.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat; stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: meringue topping
directions: Beat eggs as rapidly as possible until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar; continue beating until soft peaks form when beater is lifted.
Add sugar gradually and beat rapidly until stiff peaks form.
Spoon meringue onto hot or very warm filling.
(Meringue is less likely to weep than when baked on cold filling.)
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes.
(High temperature is best for tenderness and preventing stickiness and shrinkage.)

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add tomatoes, soup, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add beans and simmer for 30 minutes longer.

title: ra-ta-tu-tui
directions: Put everything in big pot.
Simmer for 1 hour or until tender.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and garlic salt well; pour over the vegetables.
Mix well and chill.
This makes a very pretty Christmas salad!

title: jello and cheese salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: asparagus-in-a-blanket
directions: Cut off crust of bread.
Use rolling pin and flatten remaining portion of bread.
In a bowl, combine cream cheese and Blue cheese.

title: braised short ribs of beef(with vegetables)
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Brown very slowly in hot shortening in a heavy iron skillet or Dutch oven.
For brown color and rich flavor, don't rush this step, allowing 20 to 30 minutes for browning on all sides.
Add water; cover tightly and simmer (do not boil) for about 2 hours or until tender.
Add vegetables about 30 minutes before meat is done. More water may be added, if needed, to prevent pan from going dry. Makes 4 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet until lightly browned; pour off fat.
Add catsup, water, mustard, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in long pan.
Cut sausage into pieces and place on top of rice.
Cover and cook on 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit yogurt pancake recipe
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl. Whisk together remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture. Preheat griddle, oil lightly and ladle 1/4 cup batter onto griddle for each pancake. Cook until bubbly; turn and cook until light brown.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat well.
Add beaten eggs, then sifted dry ingredients.
Chill dough. Roll thin on lightly floured board.
Cut. Sprinkle with sugar.
Decorate with bits of candied cherry.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Keep in covered tin.

title: dunkin' platters(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Melt margarine and blend with sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in cornflakes and oatmeal.
Mix flour, baking soda and baking powder; add to first mixture.
Add your choice of the next 5 ingredients using more or less of each according to your favorites.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Place far apart as will spread.
Bake 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs slightly. Add pumpkin, sugars, spices and salt.
Beat until well blended. Slowly stir in cream.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 60-70 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Just before serving, top with a dollop of sweetened whipped cream.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole and bake about 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake another 10 minutes or until a knife comes out clean when tested.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, oats, catsup, 2 tablespoons water, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Form into oval patties.
Pat in flour.
Brown in shortening in large frying pan; pour off excess grease.

title: aebleskiver
directions: Mix all together and beat egg whites separately.
Fold in last.
Makes a large batch.
Cook in Aebleskiver pan.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla and eggs. Add combined sifted cocoa and flour together. Beat well. Add nuts. Pour into a buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix meal, salt and soda together.
Add corn, shortening and eggs; beat well.
Cook ground meat; set aside.
Heat and grease large skillet.
Pour half of batter into it.
Pour meat on top of batter; sprinkle with cheese and onion and peppers.
Pour rest of batter over all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 1 cup sauce.

title: summer vegetable stew
directions: Brown the onion in butter in a large saucepan. Put the meat (cut into small pieces) over the onion. Sprinkle with salt. Add each vegetable by layers over the meat, sprinkling each layer with salt and a few tomato pieces. First add a layer of eggplant pieces. (The eggplant should be peeled and cut into large pieces), then a layer of green beans, then the squash (cut large) and then the okra. Finish by adding a last layer of quartered green peppers. Cover and cook on a very low heat for 2 hours, until meat is tender. Serve with cooked rice.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: In a bowl, cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: In blender or food processor, whirl rum, lime juice and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add strawberries; whirl until smooth. Pour into 2 chilled stemmed glasses; garnish with lime slice. Makes 2 servings.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add vanilla and baking powder; beat well.
Fold in pecans and crackers.
Pour into buttered pie plate and bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream and cool in refrigerator.

title: cookies 'n cream angel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package for angel food pan except carefully fold crushed cookies into batter.
Bake and cool as directed on package; frost cake.
Garnish with sandwich cookies.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Microwave:
Place cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart casserole with cover.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Cook, covered, 7 to 8 minutes, until about tender.
Combine and mix well the mayonnaise, mustard and onion.
Place cauliflower on serving plate and spread mayonnaise mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook, uncovered, 1 minute to melt cheese.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook for 2 1/2 minutes after coming to a boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla, stirring well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
a bowl, cream together shortening, butter and sugars.
Add egg and mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
In a bowl, sift together flour, soda and salt. Add sifted ingredients to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Place by teaspoonful on cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: choc-o-holic dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips.
Beat 4 minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake in a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes. Turn out on wire rack.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add frozen strawberries, then add pineapple. Chill 1/2 mixture in rectangular pan until firm. Spread sour cream over formed layer. Pour other 1/2 mixture over sour cream. Chill.
Keep second 1/2 out while chilling first 1/2 if it starts to set. Put bowl in warm water to dissolve.

title: five star chili
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, soup and spices.
Simmer 45 minutes, adding water if mixture gets too thick.
Add undrained beans.
Heat thoroughly.
Remove bay leaves. Good served over cornbread.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Boil cauliflower 7 to 10 minutes; drain. Melt butter. Add flour and mix well. Add chicken broth and bring to a boil. After it begins to thicken, add cheese and pastrami. Add cauliflower and pour into a 2-quart baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, butter and vinegar.
Add to well beaten eggs. Add coconut, pecans and raisins.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Melt cheese; stir in sausage.
Mix well with Bisquick.
Mold into balls and freeze.
Bake about 12 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken with stuffing
directions: Place chicken in a greased slow cooker.
Top with soup.
In a bowl combine the water, butter, and stuffing mix.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours or until chicken juices run clear.

title: nut cake
directions: Cut up fruit and coat with flour.
Mix ingredients into batter.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275° in tube pan.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just prior to serving.
Ice cubes may be made from Hawaiian punch if desired.
Add to punch.
Keep cold for serving.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in pan with floured hands and bake 10 minutes.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain. Stir in chopped chilies, seasoning mix and 3/4 cup water.
Heat to a boil, stirring frequently; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes until thickened.
Spread beans over crust.
Top with beef mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and onions to serve (taco sauce, if desired).

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
Mix mayonnaise, picante sauce and cream in small bowl.
Add vegetables to pasta.
Mix in mayonnaise mixture.
Chill well.
Makes 10 cups salad.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend all moist ingredients; mix all dry ingredients.
Mix both mixtures together.
Grease and flour 1 loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Combine flour, pudding, butter, egg and milk (or juice) in mixer bowl.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture into well-greased deep dish or casserole.
Pour drained peaches over mixture.
In another bowl, mix softened cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach juice; pour over peaches and mixture.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add flour, which has been sifted with dry ingredients, alternating with milk. Add eggs, one at a time, beating at high speed 2 minutes. Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower until crisp tender.
Drain well.
In medium saucepan, saute green pepper and mushrooms in butter for 2 minutes. Add flour, gradually stir in milk.	Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add cheeses, stir until melted.
Add pimentos and salt.	Place 1/2 of cauliflower in a greased 2 qt. baking dish.
Top with half of sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered at 325 degrees for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil to hard-ball stage.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Drizzle over 3 quarts popcorn.
Mix and make balls.

title: potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise, then cut into even wedges.
Boil potato wedges for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Pat dry.

title: easy no bake banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix pudding with milk according to package directions. Add condensed milk and Cool Whip. Mix with electric mixer. In a large serving bowl, cut bananas in bite size pieces. Add cookies. You can either layer bananas and cookies or just mix all together. Pour pudding mixture in and stir. It is best if refrigerated overnight or at least 4 or 5 hours for pudding to set. This makes a large serving and is so easy.

title: cola roast
directions: *Sirloin tip or top round do not need as much time.

title: brown elk in beer
directions: Marinate elk meat in 7-Up overnight to tenderize.
Cut elk meat in 2 x 2 1/2-inch strips.
Brown in butter or margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Add beer, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes or until meat is very tender.
Stir in gravy mix.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes longer.
Serve with rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer
first
six ingredients in order in a salad bowl. Spread mayonnaise
mixture
(next
ingredients)
on top as frosting. Top with Parmesan cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate 24 hours.	Toss before serving.

title: chloe otts' beef casserole
directions: Brown ground round in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Saut onion and green pepper in butter in small skillet. Add to ground beef with salt and noodles; mix gently. Spoon into baking dish. Combine soup, milk and cheese in saucepan. Cook until cheese melts, stirring to mix well. Pour over casserole; mix gently. Bake at 400° until bubbly. Yield: 6 servings.

title: great-grandma's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, then drain well. Put in an ovenproof 2 quart dish the margarine, Velveeta cheese, and sharp Cheddar cheese.
Add the macaroni and a little pepper, mix well.
Pour in 1 large can evaporated milk, mix well again. There should be enough milk in the dish so you can see it just below the top of the macaroni.
If not, add a little regular milk. Cover the top with bread crumbs.
Put lots of dots of margarine over the crumbs.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 45 minutes until the top starts to brown in places.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles, drain.
Brown meat and drain.
Add garlic, basil, 1 teaspoon salt and tomato sauce; simmer 20 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, eggs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Make layers of noodles, cottage cheese mixture and meat.
Makes two layers of each.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before eating.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil syrup and sugar, then add oleo and peanuts.
Boil to a hard crack and take off heat.
Add soda and beat until light brown.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet and pound on table to remove air bubbles.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: coquilles st.  jacques portugalse
directions: Sprinkle scallops with salt and pepper.
Heat oil; add scallops.
Cook over high heat, stirring about 2 minutes. Transfer scallops to baking dish.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to skillet.
When it's melted and hot add green pepper, red pepper and garlic.
Cook until wilted (about 1 minute).
Add bread crumbs, cheese and wine; heat thoroughly.
Spoon mixture over scallops.
Dot top with remaining butter and place under broiler about 4 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: brickle bars
directions: Mix sugar and butter; boil for 5 to 7 minutes.
Pour over saltines placed in a single layer in buttered baking sheet.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Place milk chocolate over crackers and spread until smooth.
Sprinkle with nuts and place in refrigerator until hard.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix chicken and rice together in chicken broth.
Cook until rice is done.
Season to taste.

title: sherbet party punch
directions: Combine concentrates and water in punch bowl.
Stir until concentrates melt.
Add ice cubes and half the sherbet.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Stir.
Just before serving, spoon in remaining sherbet.
Carefully pour ginger ale down side of bowl.
Makes about 25 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and corn.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over this and top with remaining 3 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: true chinese fried rice
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in frying pan or wok on high heat. Scramble eggs quickly and remove.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in same pan or wok.
Add eggs, rice, salt, sugar, soy sauce and broth.
Stir fry over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: bohemian stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cut the core out of the head of cabbage and put it in a medium pan with 2 cups of salted water.
Cover and boil for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Run cold water over cabbage.
Carefully peel off the cabbage leaves and set on paper towels.
In a 1-quart bowl, blend together the can of diced tomatoes, tomato soup and water; set aside.

Mix all the other ingredients together by hand and put a handful of this mixture at bottom of cabbage leaf and roll up, while folding in the sides. Place these in a large baking pan/dish or crockpot and pour tomato mixture over the top.
Makes approximately 12 to 15 cabbage rolls. Put excess cabbage on top.

title: whole wheat rolls or loaves
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in mixer bowl and turn on mixer. Add 6 cups whole wheat flour, yeast, salt and remaining flour. Knead 10 to 12 minutes.
Put into greased bowl and let rise.

title: black banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 4 ingredients together. Add both jams.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Blend in fruit and nuts.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake until done when tested with a toothpick.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out on a wire rack.
Makes a very large cake!

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: mortal sin cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Fold the whipped cream into the cheese mixture. Line bottom and sides of spring-form pan with ladyfingers. Add half of cheese mixture. Lay down another layer of ladyfingers. Add remaining cheese mixture. Top with raspberry (or other) topping. Store in refrigerator. Better if made a day early.

title: no cook cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water (strong enough to float an egg) for 7 days.
Wash and drain.
Soak overnight in alum water; wash and drain.
Put in stone container; pour 1 gallon red vinegar over cucumbers and let set 6 hours.
Drain and discard vinegar.
Layer cucumbers, spices and sugar in container.
Let stand until it makes juice.
Stir gently until sugar is dissolved.
Let stand a while; put in jars and seal.
Use 1 jar for dinner today!

title: cayuga critter eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Devine and deseed peppers.
Make small slit down pepper; stuff with shredded cheese.
Mix Bisquick and sausage thoroughly.
Press small amount of sausage mixture into 3-inch diameter by 1/4-inch thick pancake.
Make one pancake for each stuffed pepper.
Mold pancake around stuffed pepper.
In bowl, combine milk and egg.
Dip each wrapped pepper in milk, then roll in Shake 'n Bake.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.

title: melt-in-the-mouth cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light. Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by scant teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cool 1/2 minute in pan.
Then remove to rack.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Cook the eggs in hot water for 15 minutes.
Place in cold water.
Remove the shells and pack the eggs in preheated jars.
In a kettle, combine vinegar, spices and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over the eggs and seal.
Set container in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Cut crust from loaf of sliced white bread.
Roll each slice thin with a rolling pin.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions into 1/4-inch thick rings.
Separate rings and soak in milk for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Combine flour and salt into a small bag.
Shake well until coated.
Fry in deep cooking oil container.
Drain on paper towel.

title: holiday fruit punch
directions: Since I've not time to be

title: peanut butter special
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Roll mixture into small balls, about the size of walnuts.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Eat!

title: dog treats
directions: Mix flour, milk, eggs, oil, garlic powder, onion powder and salt in a large bowl.
Add cold water until very stiff.
Sprinkle flour into large square of wax paper.
Flatten the dough on wax paper with your hands.
Pinch off pieces of dough and roll them into two-inch balls.
You will probably have about 2 dozen balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Let cool to touch; peel and quarter.
Arrange sweet potatoes in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Use a 10 1/2 to 12-inch wide 1 1/2 to 2-inch deep round dish of any kind.
Prior to making dip, mix mayo, sour cream and taco seasoning mix and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Layer each item in pan in this order:
beans, avocados, mix from refrigerator, diced, peeled and seeded tomatoes, sliced scallions and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Spread rhubarb over 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with sugar. Sprinkle jello over mixture, then cake mix, oleo and water; don't mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix together with fresh cauliflower, broccoli and mushrooms. Marinate at least 4 hours.

title: melt in your mouth chicken
directions: Line a casserole dish with chicken.
In a saucepan, mix chicken broth and cream soup.
Heat and stir until smooth consistency.
Pour over chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, melted butter and buttermilk. Stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken. Cook at 425° for 30 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: quick meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup Manwich for topping meat loaf.

title: bacon cheese ball
directions: Soften	Cheddar cheese or grate it. Soften cream cheese. Mix cheeses together until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into desired shape.
Chill until firm; if desired, garnish with chopped parsley and pimento strips.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix vinegar, water and sugar.
Marinate onions in mixture overnight in refrigerator.
Drain onions, the next morning, for at least 2 hours in a colander.
Mix drained onions with salad dressing and generous amount of celery seed.
Serve on any type crackers or use for party open-faced sandwiches.
Keeps well in sealed container in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: portland popovers
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Grease 9 regular-size muffin cups well with butter or margarine; fill any remaining muffin cups with water.
Place in the oven to heat.
In a medium-size bowl, with an electric mixer set on high, beat the milk, eggs, salt, and butter or margarine until frothy.
Add the flour, beating just until smooth.
Fill the 9 muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes. Lower the heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer or until golden and set.
Serve immediately with strawberry or blueberry preserves.

title: sweet and sour pork skillet
directions: Brown pork in oil in a 10-inch skillet; drain off fat.
Drain juice from pineapple into a 4 cup glass measure; add water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add to skillet with vinegar, salt, garlic salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil, lower heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Uncover; stir in rice.
Cover, cook about 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and pork is tender.

title: homemade butter
directions: Place whipping cream in a pint jar.
Shake jar until the cream thickens.
Pour off excess
liquid and rinse with cold water. Sprinkle with salt and blend in the salt with a spoon.
Spread on bread or crackers.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add dates and nuts.
Melt over low heat about 10 minutes.
It will be thick; stir.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water and salt until tender.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add onion to broccoli and mash.
Add chicken broth, cream and cheese.
Mix well.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serves 5.
May thicken with cornstarch/water.

title: tarragon potato salad
directions: Mix all in large bowl except potatoes and blend well.
Add potatoes to mixture and mix well.
Add crumbled bacon.
Prep Time: 20 minutes plus refrigeration.
Serves 8.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Mix butter and add Hershey bar (broken up) until blended. Pour mixture into Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Will freeze well or keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer bean dip, guacamole dip, sour cream, tomatoes, olives and onions.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: easy party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 7-Up.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: This recipe was copied exactly as written in a 1909 cookbook.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine crackers, sugar, and margarine, mix well.
Press into 9-inch deep dish, pie pan plate.
In another mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, milk, lemon juice, vanilla flavoring and mix well.
Pour mixture into pie plate evenly.
Top pie with cherry pie filling and chill overnight.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Saute meat in olive oil.
Add pizza sauce, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook 10 minutes.
Spread butter on buns and brown lightly.
Spread each with meat sauce.
Top with cheese. Heat under broiler until cheese is bubbly.
Makes 8.

title: golden apple cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 2 tablespoons syrup for frosting. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Frost with Maple Flavored Frosting.

title: sweet potato hawaiian
directions: Scrub potatoes well; cut each in half.
Cook in boiling water, covered, for 20 minutes.
Leave skins on.
Drain.
When cool enough to handle, scoop potato out of shells, being careful to keep shells intact.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten whole eggs, vanilla, salt and cornmeal.
Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Increase temperature to 325°.
Continue baking for 35 minutes.

title: andrea's super oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Mix wet ingredients with sugars.
Add flours and baking soda. Mix well.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Scoop with ice cream scooper onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
For chewy cookies, do not overbake.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Shred the cabbage and cook about 10 minutes in boiling salted water.
Place in a baking dish, alternating layers of cabbage with white sauce and grated cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg and mace.
Work in butter or other shortening, as in making biscuits. Take out 1 cup of this crumbly mixture and set aside.

title: german pickles
directions: Put sliced cucumbers and onion in a gallon jar.
Pack well. Heat other ingredients until sugar is dissolved and cool completely.
Pour over cucumbers and onions; refrigerate.
You can add more cucumbers and onions to syrup as you eat pickles.

title: fruit punch
directions: Add sugar and water to taste.
Makes about 3 1/2 gallons. Will serve 60.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery with margarine until soft.
Put all ingredients in baking dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
Can be made day before.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In large bowl, cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each egg.
Sift flour, salt and soda together; add to creamed mixture.
Add sour cream and extracts.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion soup mix.
Add soups and undrained vegetables.
Put in layers the hamburger mixture, then noodles, etc.
Top with American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana-orange smoothies
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container and mix until smooth.
Makes four 8 ounce servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix cooked spaghetti, Wish-Bone dressing and McCormick Salad Supreme and refrigerate overnight.
Add remaining ingredients. The next day, mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: crispy oven potatoes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Layer potatoes in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, brushing each layer with butter mixture.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 more minutes or until cheese melts.
Yield: 6 persons.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Place sliced peaches in square baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar to taste.
Remove crust from bread slices.
Place slices on top of peaches.
Beat one egg and add to 1 stick melted margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over bread and bake at 350° to 375° until golden brown.

title: dandy dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients well; dip wieners in batter and deep fry until brown. Push a wooden stick into the end and enjoy good old dandy dogs. Best yet!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box.
Beat eggs; add soup and mayonnaise.
Tear up half the cheese into mixture.
Drain broccoli and add.
Top with rest of cheese and crumbled crackers and dot with butter.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian beans
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or put in the slow cooker for about 4 hours.

title: 30 day bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 100% Bran.
Cool.
Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Stir in bran flakes and 100% Bran.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen muffins.
Keep batter in covered container up to 30 days in refrigerator and bake as needed.

title: zucchini saute(low-fat)
directions: Saute zucchini strips in nonstick skillet with 1 teaspoon olive oil, until crisp-tender.
Add chopped tomato, minced thyme and garlic.
Cook one minute longer.

title: cheese pockets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Unroll pizza dough and cut into 12 equal pieces.
Place one teaspoon jam on each piece of dough.
Top with cheese, green onion, bacon and pecans.
Brush edges of dough with water.
Fold dough over filling and seal edges with fork.

title: savory turkey bake
directions: Mix together bouillon cubes and boiling water in a medium saucepan.
Stir until cubes are dissolved.
Stir in rice.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 20 minutes.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: roast rack of lamb with crisp herb crust
directions: Have your butcher "French" the bones of the rack of lamb and crack the ribs at the backbone for easy carving.
Trim off all fat from the meat, leaving the lean hearts of the rib chops.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: potato and ham dish
directions: Chop ham and add the 3 cans of green beans (use juice from beans), then add the potatoes (drain the juice).
Pour beef broth over top.
Season to taste.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pina colada dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl and beat until well blended.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator. Yields about 1 1/2 cups dressing. Serve on fresh fruit salads.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Use with Hawaiian bread.
Real good for parties.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix Karo and juices in pitcher.
Chill.
Just before serving, add carbonated water and pour over ice.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: easy rhubarb dessert
directions: Place rhubarb in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with the gelatin, sugar and cake mix.
Pour water evenly over dry ingredients; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rhubarb is tender.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Cook bacon crisp and crumble.
Reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Beat eggs, vinegar, water, sugar and salt until blended.
Add drippings. Cook over low heat until thick.
Store dressing and bacon in separate containers.
Use on green beans as a hot dressing and sprinkle with bacon and pimento.
Use cold as a toss salad dressing adding bacon and pimento.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter; add flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream well. Add water, cheese and red pepper.
Roll out thin on waxed paper and cut in strips or circles.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: brown rice milanese
directions: Melt the butter in a large skillet or shallow heat proof casserole over a medium heat. Add shallots and garlic, saute until tender. Add chives and dill, saute for 2 minutes. Stir in rice and saute until it begins to boil.

Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Do not remove cover during cooking time. Remove from heat and add cheese and toss lightly until melted. Rice can be cooked ahead to point of adding cheese. Heat through before adding cheese.

title: chicken and string bean casserole
directions: Mix rice that has been cooked by directions. Saute in a little oleo before mixing. Add mayonnaise with soup. Add 1 cup cheese to mixture and mix all ingredients. Put in buttered dish. Top with cheese. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. This recipe freezes well.

title: potatoes and cheese casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream and soup together.
Put 1/2 potato mix in casserole dish, then 1/2 shredded cheese and rest of potatoes.
Finish with the rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Bake 50 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: tiger butter (candy)
directions: In 2-quart bowl, place white chocolate.
Microwave on "5" for 5 to 8 minutes, until stirred smooth.
Stir in peanut butter. Spread mixture on wax paper-coated cookie sheet.

title: kid's special quick pudding cookies
directions: Combine pudding mix and biscuit mix in a medium bowl.
Stir in oil, egg and water, blending well.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheets and cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: congo bars
directions: In a bowl combine melted shortening and brown sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt, blending well. Stir in nuts and chocolate bits.

Spoon the batter (it will be thick) into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) until golden (about 40 to 45 minutes) or when a cake tester inserted comes away clean.
Remove from oven and cool in pan before cutting into bars or squares.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and shred. In 9 x 13 cake pan or casserole dish, layer the following: chicken, cheese, cream of chicken soup and diced
tomatoes (drained). Make Stove Top according to directions and put as top layer. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Great served over white rice.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Score roast in several places and fill each score with 1/2 teaspoon each salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Sear well on both sides in hot oil.
Remove roast from pan; drain off excess fat and place in foil-lined pan.
Pour cake and catsup over roast.
Cover loosely with foil and bake 3 hours at 325°.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Place chips around pan and put a layer on the bottom.
Layer ingredients in pan until all used up.
Bake in 350° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve in the pan and dive in.

title: oven steak
directions: With meat mallet (or hammer), pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness. Dredge the steak in the flour and salt. Brown steak in hot oil in large skillet.
When brown, remove from skillet.
Place in greased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Set aside. Add 2 tablespoons flour to pan (skillet) drippings.
Cook 1 minute on low heat.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots and onions.
Cook until thick.
Stir in soy sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender.

title: savory salmon dip
directions: Puree the fromage blanc and cottage cheese in a food processor or blender.
Add all other ingredients, except yogurt, blending until smooth.
Remove the mixture to a large bowl and fold in the yogurt.
Makes 3 cups.

title: egyptian eye
directions: Spray Pam in pan.
Turn stove on medium.
Take a mug or cup and put a hole in the middle of the bread slices.
(You may toast the cut-out pieces in the pan or toss.)
Put bread slices in the pan, separately.
Put an egg in each hole.
Flip over every 2 minutes or until done.

title: swedish bread yeast rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; let stand while next ingredients are mixed.
Mix next 4 ingredients and add yeast mixture.
Add flour and egg.
Mix well.
Add 3 to 4 cups flour and milk.
Mix well. Dough will be sticky.
Knead on floured surface and let sit for 10 minutes; pinch dough off for rolls.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger-mushroom bake
directions: Combine about 1/4 cup mushroom soup with onions, bread crumbs, egg, water and ground beef.
Make into patties and place into foil-lined baking pan.
Spread remainder of soup over patties and bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 10 patties. Tastes like salisbury steak.

title: turtles
directions: Microwave morsels in a glass bowl on High for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir until smooth; cool until slightly thickened.
Drop chocolate by tablespoonfuls onto a wax paper lined baking sheet, shaping into 16 (1 1/2-inch) circles.
Reserve remaining chocolate.
Arrange 4 pecans over each circle; chill until firm.
Place caramels and cream in a glass bowl; microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir after 1 minute.
Let stand.
Spoon over pecans.
Microwave chocolate on High for 1 minute.
Spread over caramels.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: basic barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients 20 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for basting 4 pounds of spareribs, chicken or beef.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo and cook chopped onion until clear.
Stir and cook broccoli until tender and stir broccoli and soup into onion. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix in Cheez Whiz and rice.
Bake in a 300° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Combine potatoes with enough sifted confectioners sugar to make fontant the consistency of pie dough.
Add vanilla.
Chill.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up from short side jelly roll fashion. Chill until firm.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Keep in a cool place.

title: sweet potatoes(from mrs. margaret wine, mt. sidney, va)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat until smooth.
Mixture will be thin.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: family rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish; stir lightly.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until rice is tender, stirring twice.

title: applesauce-carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick vegetable coating.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except the carrots.
Mix well. Add carrots and mix well.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake about 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Contains 209 calories, cholesterol is negligible, 5 grams fat and 228 sodium.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour butter over the top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, or until brown.

title: turmeric chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Mix soups together, then pour over chicken; sprinkle turmeric on top of soup.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: real baked ham
directions: Cover the ham with cold water and bring slowly to a boil. Throw out the water and replace with the cider to cover ham.
Bring this to a boil.
Lower heat, keeping the liquid barely simmering for 20 minutes to the pound of ham.
Remove from heat and allow to stand in the liquid for 30 minutes.
Take out ham; skin it and score fat with a sharp knife in a diamond pattern.
Stud with whole cloves.
Mix the sugar and mustard; rub well into ham.
Bake in a preheated oven for an additional 10 minutes to the pound in a 400° oven.
Carve; serve with sweet potatoes or a salad.

title: ohio pink stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill for 3 hours.

title: almond bark treats
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter.
Add cereal and peanuts. When the mix is not too hot, add the marshmallows.	You don't want the marshmallows to melt.
Drop with a spoon onto wax paper.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots; remove ends and cook in salted water until tender.
Cook the honey, butter and lemon juice together until it begins to boil.
Pour over the drained carrots.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: ira lee's raisin cookies
directions: Mix raisins and water.
Boil until all water is gone.
Add the soda.
Cream together in another bowl the sugar and Crisco.
Then add the eggs and beat until smooth.
Add the flour, salt and cinnamon and blend until smooth.
Add raisins.

title: cathy's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and then mix in sugar and 1 egg at a time.
Add milk alternately with flour and flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 1/4 hours in greased tube pan.
While cake is hot, glaze.

title: quick and easy pot roast
directions: Place roast in pan; add water, mushroom soup and empty contents of Lipton soup on top of roast.
Seal tight with foil.
Bake in oven set at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: baked crab spread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put into a greased casserole. Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix eggs, vinegar and water together.
Mix flour and butter together.
Shake until together, then mix eggs, water and vinegar. Shake.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend ingredients and serve with vegetables or Fritos.

title: sweet and sour baked beans(4 bean casserole)
directions: Brown onions in skillet.
Add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add onion mixture to beans. Add bacon.
Bake in a 3-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: train sandwich
directions: Mix tuna, mayonnaise, carrot, celery and pickle in a small bowl.
Fill each bun with tuna salad.
Arrange 5 buns on a long tray or board.
Cut remaining bun in half crosswise and put half on top of first bun to look like a cabin.
Place the other half on the back bun to look like a caboose.
Make wheels from the cucumber slices and smokestacks from the mushrooms.
Attach with toothpicks. Remind your children to remove the toothpicks before eating!

title: cheryl's heavenly kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry; beat in 6 tablespoons sugar, a spoon at a time. Beat until it forms peaks. Add vanilla, then fold in the rest of the sugar. Shape with spoon on cookie sheet. Bake in 250° oven for 50 minutes.
Makes about 18 or 20 kisses.

title: chicken
directions: Spray baking pan that has a baking rack with olive oil Pam. Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice (fresh) and then sprinkle with kosher salt and freshly ground pepper. Liberally sprinkle with olive oil. Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: tuna dip(hot)
directions: Rub tuna with fingers to take out lumps.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.

title: fried chicken
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Skin chicken and dip in yogurt.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Spray top of chicken with Pam.
Bake in oven at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.

title: pork tenderloin with sesame seed and mushroom sauce
directions: Slowly brown tenderloin pieces in oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; then drain off fat.
Add consomme, celery, green onions and thyme.
Cover and simmer for about 40 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove meat from skillet.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients with cream, vinegar and egg yolk.
Cook until thick.
Beat egg white until very stiff and fold into cooked mixture.

title: crawfish bisque(servings:  8)
directions: Peel, wash and cut vegetables.
Saute slightly the vegetables and the spices.
Add the crawfish and flambe with cognac.
Add white wine and cook until liquid is reduced.
Add water, whitefish and rice.
Let cook 30 minutes.
Remove a few crawfish; peel and leave the tails.
Set aside for garnish.
Strain through a China cap (small hole strainer).
Add the cream and butter to sauce. Garnish with crawfish tails.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine and refrigerate 4 hours.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with vegetables.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli according to directions on package. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, top with cheese and the chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: seven up salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cream cheese, 7-up, sugar and vanilla.
Add green food coloring and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
Drain and set	aside.	Cook all other ingredients, except onion and pepper (Put
these in raw). Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
When
warm,
pour over carrots. Add green pepper and onions.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Crumble nuts in bottom of pan. Mix all ingredients in order listed with an electric beater for two minutes.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread; spread slices with butter.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook crumbled sausage until browned, stirring; drain well.
Spoon over bread slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs and milk; mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover casserole; chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, or until set.
Yields 8 servings.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut
butter,
sugars, egg and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Press into 1
1/2-inch
muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove
from
oven
and
immediately
press
one miniature
peanut butter cup candy into each hot cookie crust; allow to cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: beer dip
directions: Place cheese in freezer until firm enough to shred easily. Shred cheese into a large bowl.
Stir in beer and a small amount of garlic powder and cayenne pepper; seasoning flavors will increase on standing.
Let stand, covered, on counter overnight. Mix well.
Adjust seasonings.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with butter crackers.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sprinkle yeast into warm water and stir until dissolved; add to shortening mixture.
Add flour; blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Dough rises slightly in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: dilled yogurt dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in blender until smooth.
Great topping for salads, vegetables or dip for crackers or chips.

title: ham swirls
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham.
Spread on ham and roll long ways.
Chill.
Cut into thin slices.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, adding chili powder to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: crown jewel salad(for christmas or easter)
directions: Boil teapot full of water.
Grease 2 loaf pans and 1 Bundt pan.
Dissolve green and red jello each in 1 cup of boiling water. Add 1/2 cup cold water to each.
Chill until set, a few hours. After an hour, dissolve lemon jello in 2 cups of boiling water in a large bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cold water; chill just until edges are set firm, about 1/2 to 1 hour.
Whip until frothy and fold in Cool Whip.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together milk and lemon juice.
Then add remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Melt butter in milk.
Beat eggs, sugar, flour and salt; add vanilla.
Pour milk into egg mixture.
Place rhubarb in unbaked 9-inch shell.
Pour milk mixture over rhubarb.
Bake at 400° for about 35 minutes or until firm.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes before slicing.
Cube
ham.
Layer
potatoes, ham, salt, pepper and cheese in a
greased
x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and milk together and pour
over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: minute swiss steaks
directions: Brown steaks in oil; remove steaks from skillet.
Stir in onion; cook until tender.
Stir in beef broth and water.
Place steaks in pan and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: chocolate mint sugar cookie drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup sugar and vegetable oil; mix well.
