Beat in eggs and vanilla extract. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in mint chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Shape into balls; roll in remaining sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: peach sour cream pie
directions: Blend sour cream, brown sugar and salt.
Whisk in well beaten egg yolks.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour on unbaked pie shell. Arrange peaches on pie shell; sprinkle with tablespoon of flour. Pour sour cream mixture over all.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for about 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: kielbasa soup
directions: Spray large saucepan with nonstick cooking spray.
Over medium heat, melt margarine in saucepan.
Add kielbasa, onion and celery; cook until onion and celery are tender.
Add carrots, cabbage, bay leaf, thyme, vinegar, bouillon cubes and water.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes; cover and cook for an additional 20 minutes.
Yield:
10 cups.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Break up cake into oblong pan.
Mix Jell-O in bowl with 2 cups hot water.
Add strawberries; mix.
Pour over cake in pan.
Let set and harden in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Mix pudding with milk.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding.
Pour mixture over cake. Refrigerate 5 to 6 hours.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Read cookie label and prepare as instructed.
As soon as cookies are taken out of oven, place one Kiss per cookie in center.
Let cool and you're bound to get a kiss for these cookies!

title: peach cheese tart
directions: Whip cheese; add condensed milk, then whip again.
Stir in lemon juice and continue beating until thickened.
Pour into the tart shell and chill.
Slice peaches and place in spiral design on top of the cheese layer.
Melt preserves with sugar.
When sugar is dissolved, pour glaze over peaches.
Top with whipped cream.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Add water and sugar in blender.
Beat 1 minute.
Add milk slowly until mixed.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer over low heat until cheese melts.
Mix well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 425°.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Saute sunflower seeds, noodles and almonds in margarine until golden brown.
(Drain excess margarine after browning.)
Add to broccoli and lettuce.
Serve topped with dressing.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and pour into a 9 x 13-inch enamel pan and let stand until firm in the refrigerator.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put graham cracker crumbs in bowl and 2 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Press mixture on bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pan.
Chill in freezer while preparing filling.
In bowl, beat cream cheese and remaining sugar until smooth and light. Beat in eggs, vanilla and cornstarch until blended.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake 10 minutes; reduce heat to 200° and bake 45 minutes.
Turn off oven and let cool for 3 hours with door slightly open.

title: mexican salad
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Add 1 package crushed Fritos just before serving.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar and spices.
Place fruit into a buttered casserole.
Pour sauce over fruit and stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: arctic melon pops
directions: In a blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into 8 (5 ounce) paper cups.
Cover each cup with foil.
Make a small hole in the foil with a knife. Insert a wooden stick into the cup through the hole.
Freeze for 4 to 6 hours or until firm.

title: frypan fruit balls
directions: Have electric skillet control at 220°.
Melt butter; add dates.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Add to dates and butter in skillet. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add fruit, nuts, Rice Krispies and flavoring.
Form into balls, roll in coconut and store in tin can in refrigerator.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Use 3 tablespoons fat and cook onion until transparent.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook until tender. Then add 2 cans undiluted cream of chicken soup and 2 cans milk. Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve garnished with crushed bacon and parsley.

title: glaze
directions: Blend in small bowl until smooth.
If too thick, stir in more milk.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix all other ingredients.
Add hamburger and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with fried bacon.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread(holiday recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9 x 5 loaf pans. Combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, soda and salt in large bowl; set aside. Combine sugar, pumpkin, eggs, vegetable oil and orange juice in large mixer bowl; beat until just blended. Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture; stir just until moistened. Fold in cranberries. Spoon batter into loaf pans. Bake for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces into baking dish.
Combine salad dressing, onion soup mix and apricot preserves.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until chicken is done.
Last 15 minutes, add pineapple and cherries.
Serve over white rice.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put in bowl squash, margarine and croutons.
Mix well.
Add onion, egg, soup and seasoning.
Mix well and bake at 350° in greased baking dish 30 minutes.

title: cheesy pork loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pate
directions: Saute livers in butter with onion until done.
Turn heat up and add brandy, salt and pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cream.
Puree all in blender.
Chill completely.
Garnish with sieved egg yolk.

title: fruit compote(6 servings)
directions: Combine all fruit and ginger ale.
Serve in sherbet dishes. Top each serving with pineapple sherbet.
Serve with plain cookies.

title: norwegian red cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage. Place in a 3-quart casserole. Add all remaining ingredients. Stir to mix. Cover.
Use cook cycle and cook 5 minutes. Stir carefully.
Cover.
Use cook cycle and cook 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Stir twice during cooking time.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ceci soup roman style
directions: Place oil, rosemary, garlic and anchovies in soup pan.
Brown well.
Add diluted tomato paste and cook over slow fire for 20 minutes.
Add ceci beans with liquid and add another can full of water.
Add salt and bring to boiling point.
Add elbow macaroni and cook 8 minutes longer or until macaroni is tender.
Add pepper and serve.
Serves 4.

title: ribs with plum sauce
directions: Cut ribs in serving size pieces.
Place in a roasting pan, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine sauce mix.
Pour over ribs and bake uncovered for 30 more minutes.

title: omelet hot dish(made the night before)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and mustard; beat well.
Add bread, cheese and sausage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle with onions, mushrooms and/or green pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package until tender, but not soft. Chop pimentos, onion and cheese.
Combine all ingredients while macaroni is still hot.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled beef kabob over rice
directions: Pour salad dressing over beef cubes in a shallow baking dish. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator, turning occasionally, for 4 hours. Alternate beef, onion, red and green peppers, zucchini and yellow squash on skewers. Grill, turning and basting with the remaining marinade, for 5 to 7 minutes or to desired doneness. Combine rice and parsley. Serve kabobs over rice.

title: tasty spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed; mix well.
Chill for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together and cook in saucepan on low heat until thickened.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients; beat in small amounts of vinegar and salad oil.
Add onion and beat thoroughly.

title: reggie's barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter and saute onions until well done.
Add tomato puree, hot sauce, vinegar, sugar and garlic powder.
Mix well. Add unseasoned barbecue sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add to cooled spinach. Refrigerate for 5 to 8 hours or overnight.
Shape into balls. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
Turn 1/2 way through baking.

title: puppy chow snack mix
directions: Melt butter, chocolate and peanut butter.
Pour this mixture over cereal and mix until covered.
Put 1/2 of powdered sugar in a brown paper bag.
Pour in the mixture and top with remaining powdered sugar.
Shake contents and let dry on wax paper.

title: lasagne
directions: In oil, brown onion and garlic; add beef.
Brown lightly. Pour off oil and fat.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, Ragu and cottage cheese.
Let simmer.
(Taste for flavor.)
Layer noodles, Mozzarella cheese, sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Start over.
End with cheese on top.
Microwave for 10 minutes on High or bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: korean vegetable dish
directions: Brown garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 1/2 hour. Add spinach and rice.
Cover tightly; cook until rice is tender, adding more water or tomato juice if needed.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
This is unusual and very tasty.

title: gracie's corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add more water if needed.
Bake in lightly sprayed iron skillet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: spicy carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
Place carrots in shallow baking dish.
Mix 1/4 cup liquid from carrots and all ingredients except the Ritz crumbs, butter and paprika.
Put the mixture on top of carrots.
Melt the butter and mix the Ritz crumbs into it.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Sprinkle paprika on top of all.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tuna rice skillet
directions: Cook first three ingredients in butter in large skillet, drain mushrooms, reserving liquid. Add water to liquid to make 2 cups. Pour into skillet, Stir in mushrooms, rice, tuna, salt/pepper and bouillon, mix well. Bring to a boil, add peas, cover and simmer over low heat 20 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring once or twice.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Add vanilla. Drop by spoonful on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Dissolve sugar and red hots in 1 quart of warm water.
Add other ingredients and 2 more quarts water.

title: coconut-chocolate meringue bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix butter, brown sugar, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes. Blend flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix thoroughly together with egg mixture.
Spread or pat dough into pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top and press into dough. Beat egg whites; gradually add 1 cup brown sugar and beat until stiff.
Mix coconut with egg white mixture.
Spread on top of dough over nuts and chips.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a large, heavy pan.
Boil to 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add margarine. Stir until dissolved, then slowly add cream.
Put back on heat, stirring and watching closely.
Cook rapidly to 250°.
Remove from heat and add nuts and vanilla.
If curdles, stir or beat a minute or so, then pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares and wrap.

title: sole with shrimp and butter sauce
directions: In a baking dish, stir in the wine, butter and onion.
Add the fish fillets sprinkled with salt and pepper.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove fish from oven and place on 4 serving plates.
Reserve the liquid; add to the shrimp and spoon the sauce over the fillets.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: fresh picante sauce
directions: Place jalapenos into blender with 1 cup water.
Blend until coarsely chopped.
Drain.
Put 1/2 can of tomato sauce into blender with garlic and onion. Blend.
Add drained jalapeno, remainder of tomato sauce, tomatoes and the rest of ingredients. Turn blender off and on quickly until blended, but leave tomatoes chunky.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, vinegar and well beaten eggs.
Mix well; add raisins, pecans and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put stew meat, onion, carrots, tomatoes and green beans in water and cook until meat is tender.
Add potatoes, limas and whole kernel corn.
After everything in soup gets done, add peas and let soup simmer for about 1 hour.

title: alcohol free-welsh rarebit
directions: Melt butter and add seasonings and cheese.
Stir in double boiler until cheese is soft.
Add ginger ale and then egg.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Serve over toast.
Serves 3.

title: beer pretzels
directions: Mix beer, yeast and sugar together until yeast is dissolved and foamy.
Add flour; mix well.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Cover a cookie sheet with foil and grease well.
Punch dough down; break off walnut sized pieces of dough and roll into rope, then shape into pretzel.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 475° about 12 minutes.
Best eaten while still warm as the pretzels get tough as they sit.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add chips. Mix remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Fill cupcake tins 1/2 full of chocolate mixture.
Then spoon in 2 tablespoons of cream cheese mixture. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: cheesy stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Pierce potato.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes until tender, turning the potato over halfway through cooking.
Cut in half, scoop out center of potato.
Mash with butter, milk, cheese and salt and pepper.
Put back in peel, microwave for 1 minute.

title: frosty chocolate pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add 1 cup syrup and milk, beating until blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour mixture into crust.
Freeze several hours or overnight.
(Wrap pie after partially frozen.) Serve topped with chilled syrup.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
tags: graham cracker crumb crust pie shell

title: jam cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Beat in Crisco and jam.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately. Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 4 (9-inch) layers.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain and set aside.
Separate dough into triangles.
Place points to center of 12-inch pizza pan; press to form crust.
Spoon sausage over top.
Sprinkle with hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; pour over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese; bake 5 minutes more.

title: blueberry crunch cheesecake
directions: Mix and pat onto pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Beat at low speed.
Gradually add sugar; stir in 1/2 cup nuts.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook sliced onion and pepper in fat until soft, then add bay leaf, cloves, tomatoes, sugar and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice.
Bake in casserole about 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all ingredients except beans.
Cook 1 to 2 hours in crock-pot.
During last half-hour, add beans. Serves 8 to 10.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Serve in hollowed-out bread or with crackers.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all but 1 cup of the cake mix with 1 egg and 1/2 cup oleo. Spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix the pumpkin, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 eggs, 1 can milk and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; pour over first layer.
Mix the last cup of dry cake mix with 1/4 cup oleo, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; spread over pumpkin layer as top layer.
Bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Don't heat anything. Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Mix all together and place in glass jar in refrigerator. Liquid will not cover cucumbers fully, but will by morning.
Keep refrigerated.
Can add more vinegar as you use cucumbers, if desired.

title: swing shift soiree
directions: Cut up the 4 hot dogs into 1/2-inch pieces and place in a medium size saucepan.
Saute on medium heat for a few minutes or until the edges are slightly brown.
Lower the heat to the minimum setting on your stove.
Pour in the baked beans; stir.
Pour in the remaining liquid ingredients; stir.
Allow the mixture to slowly simmer for approximately 1 hour or until the blend has a consistency of molten lava.

title: crusty fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, garlic salt, salt, celery salt, pepper and paprika in paper or plastic bag.
Add a few pieces of chicken at a time.
Shake to coat.
Heat oil to 365° in electric skillet or on medium-high heat in large heavy skillet.
Fry chicken 30 to 40 minutes without lowering heat.
Turn once for even browning.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini and drain.
Cool.
Add other ingredients and mix.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in medium size bowl.
Stir in egg, onion and cayenne pepper.
Add buttermilk; beat well.
Heat lard in heavy frypan until hot, about 375°.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of batter into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Wrap hush puppies in heavy foil; place in warm oven (250°) until ready to serve.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: venison pasty
directions: Mix pie crust as directions show only use milk instead of water and add 1 tablespoon oleo.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts; roll out into 4 circles.

title: silverado taco casserole
directions: In lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, place one-half taco chips.
Set aside.
In 10-inch skillet, brown beef until crumbled. Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in onion and tomato sauce.
Spoon meat mixture over taco shells.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Place remaining taco chips over cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Arrange tomato wedges and olives attractively on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with taco sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken until tender.
Bone and chop.
Strain chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti in stock until tender.
Drain and reserve the stock.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients into mixing bowl except coconut.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Add toasted coconut; fold in well.
Pour mixture into 9-inch pie crust.
Place on cookie sheet to bake.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: special fried rice
directions: After water starts to boil add 2 cups rice to soy sauce, bouillon and sesame oil and cook until done.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients with sour cream and mashed bananas.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Drain beans; mix all ingredients together.
Taste.
Add more sugar and vinegar or oil according to your taste.
(I use a full can of each type of beans.)
Let stand and cool in refrigerator.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and roll into balls and dip into white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
They will flatten and crack as they bake.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat milk; add rice and fat.
Ad sugar, salt and raisins or nuts to eggs.
Slowly stir in hot milk mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish; set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: finger-licking spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season ribs with salt and pepper to taste.
Place in roasting pan, cover with aluminum foil.
Roast 1 hour.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Mix well. Stir in flour and nutmeg.
Dissolve soda in hot water, add to banana mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fill greased muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 24 medium muffins.

title: boston brown bread
directions: In large bowl put dates, butter and baking soda.
Add boiling water and mix well allowing to cool completely.
Add eggs, sugar, salt, flour and vanilla and beat well.
Fold in nuts.
Half fill greased cans (use 6 to 7 1-pound vegetable cans).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: good cake
directions: Prepare German chocolate cake mix according to directions on box. Cool slightly.
Poke holes in cake with handle of a wooden spoon. Dribble the Eagle Brand milk in the holes.
Pour the caramel sauce in holes.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle crushed Heath bars or chopped walnuts on top. Refrigerate
until
ready to serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together, roll out and cut 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for about 8 minutes.

title: president tyler's pudding pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a deep bowl, mix the butter, sugar and light brown sugar together.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time, and when they are thoroughly mixed, stir in the heavy cream and vanilla.
Pour the filling into the pastry shell and dust the top evenly with the cinnamon and nutmeg mixture.

Bake in the center of the oven for about 50 minutes until the filling has just begun to set. It will be slightly soft in the middle but will become firm as it cools. Remove from oven and cool to room temperature.
Cool well before cutting.

title: uncooked chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together over hot water.
Combine the egg, sugar and milk and mix well.
Add the melted chocolate and butter and mix well.
Add the vanilla and nuts.
Place in a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and chill well in the refrigerator. Cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: chocolate chunk banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir eggs, bananas, oil and milk until well blended.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir until just moistened.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Soak cucumbers in the lime in enough water to cover the cucumbers for 24 hours.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Make sure it is dissolved good.
I dissolve the sugar and vinegar overnight.

title: fresh vegetable marinate
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; toss lightly.
Combine remaining 7 ingredients; mix well and pour over vegetables. Chill at least 3 hours. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil 4 to 6 chicken breast halves until well done; remove meat from bone and chop.
Using margarine, saute onion (chopped) and bell pepper (diced).
Add chili powder and salt and pepper, as desired.
Add cream of tomato soup (undiluted) and cream of chicken soup (undiluted).
Simmer for 30 minutes.
(If the sauce seems too thick, dilute with chicken broth).
Cook one 8 ounce package of spaghetti.
Combine sauce, chicken and spaghetti and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until hot and cheese is bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: **Or 2 cans cream of mushroom or 2 cans cream of chicken or 1 can cream of celery soup with 1 of the other soups.

title: honey bun bars
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add water and blend until a dough forms.
With floured fingers, press on bottom of greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Drizzle honey over crust; spread slightly.

title: egg custard
directions: Whip eggs.
Add salt; then add sugar and flour.
Sift nutmeg, add milk, flavoring, and butter last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 250° until thick and well done.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not preheat oven.
Cook at 450° until lightly browned.
Refrigerate unused dough.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs together.
Blend together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: malasada(doughnut without the hole)
directions: Dissolve yeast and let stand until other ingredients are mixed.
Measure flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl (the large Tupperware bowl is perfect).
Mix cream and water together; add to dry ingredients.
Add the melted butter and beaten eggs.
Add the dissolved yeast and stir.
Mix well to form soft dough.
Cover and place in warm place.
Let it stand until it doubles in size (about 2 hours).
Drop spoonfuls in hot oil, fry until light brown. Drain on brown paper bag, then roll in sugar.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: carrots almondine
directions: Cut carrots in thin 1/2 inch strips.
Heat 6 Tbsp. butter in pan.
Add carrots. Cover and cook on low heat until slightly tender. Make a cream sauce of 2 Tbsp. butter, flour and milk. When sauce thickens, add bitters, sugar and salt.
Pour over carrots and almonds.

title: roast-in-foil
directions: Use heavy foil.
Place roast on foil.
Brush with steak sauce and
sprinkle
onion
soup mix.
Add the mushroom soup. Close foil tightly.
Roast at 300° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 275° and cook 2 hours more!
Do not open oven.
No peeking!!

title: cream cheese pie filling
directions: Have cream cheese room temperature, then mix powdered sugar and cream cheese together until fluffy.
Add whipped cream and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with favorite fruit filling.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast meat uncovered at 350° about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Cool and slice.
Add water to pan drippings.
Stir in seasonings and green peppers.
Simmer 15 minutes (do not allow to boil)
Put sliced beef into this mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Reheat to serve.

title: mrs. ponsetta's hungarian cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage, onions, tomato juice and kraut.
Parboil cabbage a few leaves at a time until wilted.
Shape mixture into oval shapes (size of a bar of soap) and wrap into cabbage leaf.
Place rolls into a 5 quart cooker sprayed with Pam. Spread sauerkraut on top with onion rings.
Put several leaves of cabbage on top and pour tomato juice over it.
Boil for 2 hours, 1 hour at medium heat and 1 hour at low heat.
Serves 13.
These are truly delicious.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Dust chicken with flour, salt and pepper. Saute garlic and mushrooms with 4 tablespoons butter, then add dusted chicken and 3 more tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Cook until brown on both sides. Remove chicken and mushrooms.
Blend flour into remaining butter and oil.
Add sherry, cream and cheese. Once cheese is melted, add your cooked chicken and sun-dried tomatoes. Cook low for about 25 minutes. Serve over cooked pasta.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and sausage; drain fat.
Add spices to taste and all tomatoes, mix in and bring to boil.
Let simmer 15 minutes. Add all ingredients, then layer in 2 pans.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: bami
directions: Boil chicken and tear into small pieces. Save stock.
Cook noodles in chicken stock.
In chicken fat or margarine, brown garlic and onions. Add all other ingredients except noodles. Simmer about 10 minutes until almost done. Combine mixture with noodles.
Let it sit overnight for best flavor.
Heat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with soy sauce. Serves 8.

title: margaritas
directions: Using limeade can for measuring ingredients, combine in blender.
Fill blender almost to top with crushed ice.
Blend until thoroughly mixed, about 1 minute.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: In small bowl, put 1 cup water, sugar and yeast.
Set aside to dissolve, then in large bowl, put 2 cups water, 3/4 cup sugar, shortening, eggs and salt.
Mash potatoes and dissolved yeast water, then stir in flour.
Knead about 5 minutes.
Put in large bowl and let rise 1 hour.
Roll out dough and cut doughnut out. Let rise about 1 hour or so, then cook in hot oil until golden brown.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package and drain.
In saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat and gradually stir in flour.
When thickened, stir in cream.
Add 1/2 cup of cheese and stir until melted.
Fold in spinach, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle top of pie with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: ginger spiced sesame chicken
directions: Slice chicken into thin strips.
In large plastic bag (1 gallon) combine flour and sesame seed.
Shake chicken pieces, a few at a time, in mixture until well coated.
Brown over medium-high heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add ginger, peppers, pea pods and soy sauce.
Cook about 5 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Serve with rice.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry up bacon to crisp texture, drain, crumble.
In same pan brown ground meat, onion, salt, pepper.
Drain.
In a casserole, mix all ingredients.
Bake in 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: golden turkey breast
directions: Place turkey breast in a shallow baking pan.
Pour the chicken stock, wine and lime juice over it.
Sprinkle the sugar (if you are using it) over the turkey and into the liquid.
Arrange onion slices around the turkey.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours or until the turkey is tender, basting every 1/2 hour.
Add the raisins for the last 10 minutes of cooking.
Remove skin before serving, if desired.

title: "cheesy green bean pasta"
directions: Drain green beans.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine green beans and liquid with remaining ingredients.
Heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach-almond pound cake
directions: Cream the butter. Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Combine sour cream and peaches. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture with peach mixture.
Mix just until blended. Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans. Cool.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: 1. Cream butter, add sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. 2. Add dry ingredients, divide dough in half.
Roll out dough between wax paper till about 10 x 12-inch. 3. Chill in freezer till firm. 4. Spread filling, roll tightly lengthwise in wax paper.
Put in fridge for 30 minutes.
Easier to cut. 5. Remove paper & cut in 1/8-inch slices. 6. Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes. 7. These cookies will not be brown on edges when done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini, onion, oregano, tomatoes and mushrooms, if desired.
Cook until tender, uncovered.
There should be plenty of liquid from the vegetables.
Add tomato sauce and Parmesan cheese. Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Last 5 minutes sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: layered mint chocolate candy
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with 1 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread half the mixture into wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan; chill 10 minutes or until firm.
Hold remaining chocolate mixture at room temperature.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt coating with remaining sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in peppermint extract and food coloring if desired.
Spread on chilled chocolate layer; chill 10 minutes longer or until firm.
Spread reserved chocolate mixture on mint layer.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: uncle chuck's old fashioned navy bean soup
directions: Wash and sort the beans.
Soak in 2 cups cold water overnight.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until done.

title: 5-hour stew
directions: Do not brown meat. Combine all ingredients and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: aunt mack's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks and 1 large can of milk and 1 can of water.
Cook until thickens.
Add the vanilla. (May add more cocoa, if desired.)
Make meringue from egg whites. Use 2 tablespoons sugar to each egg white.

title: crusty herbed cauliflower
directions: Cut cauliflower into medium-size flowerets.
Cook in steamer basket over simmering water in covered saucepan for 15 to 18 minutes or just until tender.
Remove.

title: tomato apple chutney(makes 12 half pints)
directions: Chop fine the tomatoes, apples, onions and green peppers.
I put them through the blender or chop with some of the vinegar for liquid.
Combine both raisins, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag and add.
Boil 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove spice bag.
Ladle into 1/2 pint jars boiling hot.
Seal at once.
Cool and label.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Crush graham crackers up fine in a Ziploc bag then put 1/2 in the bottom of 13 x 9 cake pan.
Then whip cream cheese and whip topping in large bowl.
Put half of it in on top of the graham cracker crumbs.
Put blueberry pie filling on top of the cream cheese mixture then put the rest of the cream cheese on top of the pie filling.
Then put the rest of the graham cracker crumbs on top of it.
Put in refrigerator overnight or for a couple of hours.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cheese and garlic salt.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Wrap bacon around bread stick.
Place on cookie sheet with parchment paper on it.
Bake for 15 minutes or until the bacon browns.
Remove and roll in cheese mixture.
Let cool before serving.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per package directions.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Mix together cheeses, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until fork comes out clean.

title: corn soup
directions: Boil stew meat and onion until tender.
Add corn and tomato sauce.
Season to taste.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: On medium heat, melt brown sugar, sugar and corn syrup, stirring until sugar dissolves. Add peanut butter and flavoring. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies. Spoon teaspoon-size onto wax paper to cool, then roll into balls.

title: classic baked pasta casserole(makes 12 to 15 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Prepare pasta as package directs. In large bowl, combine pasta, sausage, pasta sauce and 2 cups cheese. Mix well. Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish; cover. Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Uncover; top with remaining 2 cups cheese and parsley. Bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sausage bites
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water.
Mix sausage and cheese with Bisquick and broth until it forms a ball.
Make into 1-inch balls and bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Heat to serve.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Chop 3/4 cup walnuts coarsely; chop remaining 1/4 cup fine for tops of brownies.
Re-sift flour with baking powder.
Combine butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
(Mixture will appear slightly curdled.)
Stir in chocolate syrup then flour mixture. Add coarsely chopped walnuts.
Turn into greased 8-inch square baking pan; spread level.
Sprinkle with finely chopped walnuts. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes until top springs back when lightly touched and pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan. Cut into squares or bars and serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter and sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into lightly greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pasta e'fagiole
directions: Soak the beans overnight in 3 cups water.
Saute sausage; add to bean water.
Cook until beans are soft, but not mushy.
Add seasonings, broth and tomato sauce; simmer just until flavors blend.
This can be made one day in advance.
Before serving, cook pasta and refresh with cold water before adding to bean mixture. If added while hot, pasta will absorb too much of the liquid.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef and onions into a microwave-safe colander and place in a glass pie plate.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes uncovered.
Drain.
Layer 1 cup taco chips on bottom of 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish.
Cover with ground beef, taco seasoning mix, tomatoes (cut in quarters), sour cream and cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Microwave on High uncovered 5 to 6 minutes until cheese melts.

title: knorr's spinach dip
directions: Mix together soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add drained spinach, scallions and water chestnuts, mixing well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Hollow out loaf of bread.
Fill hollow with dip. Cut hollowed out bread into cubes for dipping.
Serve immediately.

title: yuk
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Pour pudding over cake.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate until pudding is set.

title: cottage cheese squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco.
Put 1 egg yolk in cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Stir into sugar-Crisco mix.
Make 2 balls.
Roll one to fit a cookie sheet.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Cook in crock-pot for 4 hours on low or 3 hours on high.
Remove lid.
Add oleo; stir with fork. Let set a few minutes.

title: chicken atop rice
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in oblong pan.
Mix water and soup. Pour over rice mixture.
Arrange chicken breasts on top of rice. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, paprika and poultry seasoning.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° uncovered.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas, then flour, salt, soda and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour in 300° oven in a loaf pan.

title: 22 minute cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, combine and bring to a boil shortening, butter, cocoa and water. Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla to the mixture and mix well.
(Mixture will be thin.) Pour in a greased cake pan and bake for 22 minutes at 400°.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except lemon juice.
Cook in a large
double boiler on slow heat for 3 hours.
Add lemon juice. This will
fill
or more tart shells.
Use the egg whites for meringue.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Blend sugar, flour and salt.
Add to milk and cook over low heat, about 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and add to hot mixture.
Remove from stove and add butter and vanilla. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Put in oven about 5 minutes for meringue to lightly brown.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Boil water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Then combine chilled syrup, pineapple juice, lemonade and cranberry juice.
Chill.
Just before serving, pour juice over ice and mix ginger ale or lemon lime soda.
Serves 60.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Mix well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Chill well.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick; cut out.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add garlic, parsley and wine.
Heat at a simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Serve over bed of rice or over favorite pasta.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix beans, taco seasoning and sauce with ground beef.
Spread sour cream on top and add cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Eat with nacho chips or spoon into taco shells.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend well with electric mixer. With spoon, stir in dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add Rice Krispies and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade concentrate with Eagle Brand milk and slowly blend in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate for 2 hours and serve.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Set oven to 400° (I used 350°).
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Spread chicken and vegetables evenly in dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in small bowl; pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine mix, milk and butter; stir until smooth. Pour mixture over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed bell peppers(delicious!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut tops of bell peppers and remove seed.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill peppers with mixture and bake in baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes. Recipe makes 4 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: karen's lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add Ragu, oregano and salt. Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix cheeses and parsley.
Layer in 2-quart Pyrex dish the noodles, cheese and sauce.
Repeat, ending with meat.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lo-cal hot spiced cider
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine cider and sweetener.
Combine spices and place in a tea strainer or tie in cheesecloth.
Place in saucepan.
Bring to boil over low to medium heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.
Serves 8. Equals 1 fruit exchange.

title: rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar, salt and shortening; scald but don't boil. Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over yeast in large bowl.
Let yeast dissolve.
Add egg and flour; let rise to double in size.
Roll out and cut into rolls.
Let rise in pan, then bake at 350° until brown.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts. Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix all together in punch bowl and serve.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: norwegian pancake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 375° preheated oven.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a blender.
Transfer immediately to the 9 x 13-inch pan that has been preheated with the butter melted into it.
Do not let the blended ingredients sit in the blender. It must go right from blender to pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Slice in pan and serve with powdered sugar or syrup.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons sugar and coat blueberries.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Cool.
Remove skins and grate on a cheese grater. Add all of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and place 6 tortillas in bottom, then cheese, onion, chicken and remaining ingredients (made into sauce).
Layer 2 more times, ending with sauce.
Bake 30 minutes to one hour at 350°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together in ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti according to directions. Place hot spaghetti in a large bowl and toss with butter.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs; toss.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a well-greased 10-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: ernie's mexican chef's salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss with cheese, dressing and hot sauce.
Crunch and add Doritos.
Slice and add the avocado.
Brown meat.
Add beans and salt or garlic salt to taste to ground beef.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix with cold salad.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat everything together with mixer.
Grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked venison roast
directions: Wash meat thoroughly, being sure that all excess fat is trimmed off.
Pat dry and place in baking pan that has been lined with enough foil to wrap the meat in at least 2 layers of foil and you have room on the ends to seal tightly.
Place meat in foil; rub generously with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle all over with onion mix, pepper and garlic powder.
Place onion slices all over top of roast.
Pour wine in bottom of foil and seal tightly.
Cook at 325° no less than 3 hours.
Do not peek!

title: blueberry cake
directions: Make cake according to box directions.
Let cool.
Cut into four layers.

title: "tipsy" sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk, bourbon and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine brown sugar and remaining 1/3 cup butter and flour.
Mix well together and add nuts.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great dish for the holidays!

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with additional wheat germ.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Scald milk and set aside to cool.
Beat egg white until stiff. Set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, cream sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add egg white, cooled scalded milk and vanilla.
Beat at high speed until creamy and all sugar is dissolved.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in an 11 x 15-inch pan. Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Add baking powder to egg whites; beat until stiff.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating at high speed until sugar dissolves.
Add Ritz crackers (crumbled with hands).
Fold them into egg whites. Add chopped pecans and vanilla.
Pile mixture into a well buttered pie plate (not too near edge).
Bake 30 minutes at 325°. When completely cool cover with whipped cream and dry instant cocoa.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 to 20 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: slush
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Blend sugar and warm water; bring to
a boil.
Add to Jell-O mixture and cool.
Add lemonade, undiluted, and pineapple juice.
Freeze in several containers. Remove from freezer several hours before serving.
Mix with ginger ale and serve.

title: chicken spread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: stuffed squash with cheese sauce
directions: Wash squash; cut off and discard stem.
Cut squash in half lengthwise and scoop out seeds.
In medium skillet with tight fitting cover, bring 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon of salt to boil. Add squash, cut side down, and cook over medium heat 5 minutes or until tender (but not mushy).
Drain well.

title: rice crispy bars
directions: Melt margarine in lrg. pan over low-med. heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Cook 3-4 min., stirring constantly.
Add crispies.
Press into buttered cake pan or onto a piece of wax paper.
(When you go to press it down, run cold water and wet hands with water as you press down, this will keep it from sticking to your hands.)

title: caraway carrot slaw
directions: In bowl, mix well the mayonnaise, buttermilk, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Stir in carrots, celery and onions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl if desired.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Place chicken in bottom of crock-pot.
Combine dry spaghetti sauce mix with wine; pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 7 hours.
Turn control to high and add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes or until tomatoes are done.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cabbage delight
directions: Layer cabbage, potatoes, onions and sausage in pot.
Add small amount of water, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender. Ready in no time.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and remove bone; chunk chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and water (add) until tender.
Tenderize celery, bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Add to spaghetti (not too much liquid in spaghetti after it's tender). Add salt, pepper, paprika and Worcestershire to taste.
Mix together all ingredients into casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potato and ham casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Chop ham.
Arrange potatoes, onion and ham in layers, dotting each layer with margarine, salt and pepper.
Heat milk and mushroom soup, stirring to mix.
Pour mixture over layered ham and potatoes.

title: blueberry-banana pie
directions: Bake pie shells.
Let cool completely.
Slice bananas into bottom of pie shells.
Cream together sugar and cream cheese. Spread over layer of bananas.
Spread pie filling over cream cheese.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Better if overnight.

title: superb stroganoff
directions: Brown steak strips in skillet.
Remove steak from skillet and set aside.
Add onions and mushrooms to skillet and saute until onions are tender.
Add meat, sour cream, parsley and seasonings. Stir over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Place noodles on serving platter and top with meat and sauce mixture.
Serves 4.

title: grits with cheese
directions: Boil grits with 1 stick butter and 1 quart milk until thick. Remove from fire; add cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat with a mixer to blend, adding 1/3 stick melted butter on top.
Put in a greased casserole and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: favorite veggie dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate. Serve with fresh vegetables for dipping.

title: mongie's tart squares
directions: With electric mixer beat together margarine, sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla until well blended.
Dough will be creamy. Spread onto ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Score into 24 sections.
Drop pie filling by the spoonful onto each square.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes to 45 minutes.
Browns quickly.
When cooled, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: corn relish
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. After cooling, refrigerate several days.

title: scott's delicious french toast
directions: Heat a skillet sprayed with Pam.
Mix the milk, egg and salt; dip the bread in this mixture.
Fry until brown on each side. Serve with syrup.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: When egg whites are frothy, add baking powder.	Fold in sugar and
teaspoons
vanilla, beating well.
Add nuts and crumbled graham
crackers.
Bake
in
greased
pie pan.
Whip cream and add sugar and vanilla to taste.
Spread over pie and let
stand several hours so the cream weeps in the pie.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: date roll
directions: Place sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Increase heat and boil to a soft ball.
Stir in cut up dates and cook for 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and beat until thick; add nuts and roll in foil.

title: perked punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bottom of percolator.
Place spices in basket and perk.
Keep warm until serving time.

title: snowballs(fudge)
directions: Melt chocolate and milk together, slowly mix in 2 cups sugar. Reserve the rest.
With greased palm (use butter or margarine) roll into 1-inch balls.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar and chill.

title: pecan rum pie
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart dish glass measuring cup.
Blend in nuts, sugar, corn syrup, egg and rum.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes until center is set.
Cool.
Serve warm with whipped or ice cream.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Wilt onions in oil. Add all other ingredients, except shrimp. Cook for 1 hour over low heat. Add shrimp about 20 minutes before cooking time is completed. Serve over rice.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and oleo; add egg yolks, one at a time. Add milk and flour a little at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Gently stir in pecans and coconut.
Combine soda and buttermilk and let stand a few minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in cream mixture.
Cook at 325° in 3 (9-inch) pans for 25 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and chill.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions together; drain. Combine all ingredients into large kettle and cook on medium temperature for about 30 minutes. Top with shredded cheese and serve with nachos.

title: potato wedges
directions: Scrub and slice potatoes.
Each potato will make 6 to 8 wedges.
Melt margarine in a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix the dry ingredients together and place in a plastic bag or plastic bowl.
Add potatoes a few at a time and shake, coating well, and place in pan in a single layer.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Turn and bake 20 minutes more.
Wedges should have a medium-brown, crispy coating when done.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and water chestnuts.
Bake in casserole dish at 420° for 20 minutes. Remove.
Add pimentos, chopped eggs and rest of cheese to top. Heat 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll pizza dough and bake according to directions.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion powder, garlic powder and dill weed.
Spread over pizza crust.
Put diced vegetables on top of mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and serve.
(Cut pizza crust before adding vegetables.)

title: cheesy button appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and butter; stir in water and sesame seed until dough ball forms.
Drop by teaspoonful into cheese; coat dough with cheese.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 7 to 10 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Stir butter and Cheez Whiz into 1 cup boiling water until melted. Mix other ingredients and add Cheez Whiz mixture. Stir well. Pour into a greased casserole dish (3 1/2-quart). Bake at 350° until done. Casserole will be "solid" in the middle.

title: chicken broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts with celery until tender.
Let cool and pull off bones in small chunks.
Layer ingredients as follows: chicken, rice, broccoli, water chestnuts, cheese and soup (may be slightly diluted, if necessary).
Cook for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: avocado dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Process at blend until smooth.
Serve on lettuce and tomato salad.

title: trifle bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
After cake has cooled, pull apart into medium size pieces and make a layer in your trifle bowl.
Add a layer of Cool Whip and drizzle with syrup.
Continue to repeat layers until all of the cake has been used.
After final layer of Cool Whip, decorate with colored sprinkles.

title: mississippi mud cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper and let harden.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Cool.
Punch holes in and pour Kahlua in brownies; set aside.
Whip up jello chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces.
Break up 1/2 of the brownies and place in the bottom of a glass trifle dish.
Cover with half of the mousse and then layer with half of the candy and then add half of the whipped topping.
Repeat layering.

title: five cup salad
directions: In a bowl, combine orange sections, pineapple chunks, coconut, marshmallows and sour cream.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: cold lettuce dressing
directions: Can make and store in refrigerator.

title: italian chicken in garlic bread
directions: Roll out the thawed bread dough to a 15 x 10-inch rectangle and place on a large greased baking pan or cookie sheet.

In a large frying pan, saute onions in the olive oil for 3 minutes. Add green pepper, chicken, mushrooms, garlic, wine and spaghetti sauce, cooking on medium heat about 12 to 15 minutes or until chicken is done and liquid is reduced. Mix butter with garlic salt.
Baste the rolled out bread dough with half of the butter mixture.
Then sprinkle 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese evenly over the dough.
Spread the chicken mixture evenly over the cheese.
Roll up the bread dough lengthwise, sealing the sides and ends.

Place the loaf, seam side down, on the baking sheet. Baste the rolled loaf with most of the remaining butter mixture. Sprinkle the remaining Parmesan cheese along the top of the loaf. Let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Using any remaining butter mixture, baste the sides and top of the cooked loaf after removing from the oven.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: To prevent soggy crust, prick pie shell with a fork before baking.
Bake at 325° for a few minutes before adding filling.

title: ambra's hot rolls
directions: Heat water, margarine and milk until margarine melts (in microwave approximately 1 minute and 45 seconds).
Add liquid mixture to 4 cups of the flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
Mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Add 1 more cup of flour and mix with mixer.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups of flour, a little at a time, and knead with hands.
Knead about 5 minutes either on flat surface or if using a large bowl, you can knead it in the bowl. Let rise in warm place until double (approximately 1 hour).

title: melting moments
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, add cornstarch, sugar and flour; mix thoroughly.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place one inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on racks, frost.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter. Boil 2 cups water and add potatoes and spices. Boil for 15 minutes. Cut fish into cubes. Add to mixture and boil again for 10 minutes. Add milk and heat.

title: veal amelio
directions: Pound veal gently with wooden mallet.
Sprinkle very lightly with flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat olive oil and 2 tablespoons butter.
When pan is hot saute veal on both sides without browning.
Remove and set aside, keeping veal warm.
Add wine to pan and heat slightly.
Add remaining butter and lemon juice.
Saute mushrooms briefly.
Place several veal slices on each plate and top with mushrooms and sauce.
Serve a salad, buttered fettucini and snow peas or asparagus.

title: applesauce cake(diabetics)
directions: Cook raisins in a small amount of water until dry.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk for 1 minute or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in whipped topping, pecans, gingersnaps, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight until firm.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand for about 20 minutes to soften before serving.

title: sweet potato bread(for large batch)
directions: In a large crock, combine first 5 ingredients and mix well. In separate bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Stir dry ingredients gradually into liquid mixture until thoroughly blended. Fold in nuts.
Pour batter in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or 12 or more small loaf pans as I do for Canaan Fall Festival and other flea markets.
Bake at preheated 300° 1 hour and 20 minutes or until bread tests done with toothpick. Delicious and moist!

title: microwave peach crisp
directions: Arrange peaches in square microwavable dish (8 x 8 x 2-inches). Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn and microwave, uncovered, until peaches are tender, 4 to 6 minutes or longer.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired. Serves 6.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash bananas in mixing bowl. Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pour mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage-squash casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onion until brown; drain off fat.
Stir squash and next 5 ingredients into meat mixture.
Fold in eggs; bake in casserole dish for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: meat loaf patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into patties (4).
Broil or panfry as desired.

title: you make it shake and bake
directions: Stir together in an airtight container and store in refrigerator until needed.
Use on chicken or pork chops.
Rinse meat and dip in portion of coating mix on both sides.
Bake meat in oven with a little butter in bottom of pan.
Turn meat over halfway through baking.

title: myrtle faircloth's orange cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Use 3 or 4 round 9-inch pans, greased and lightly floured.
Fill each pan 1/2 full with batter.
(Layers will be thin.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Make frostings (recipes follow).

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Reduce or add more ingredients to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bacon.
Add other ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles.
Melt butter and mix in soup and cheese.
Add noodles; stir and cook in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chestnuts in tomato sauce
directions: Wrap chestnuts in bacon and stab with toothpicks.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Bake bacon wrapped chestnuts on cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°.
Turn and bake 10 more minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, put Tater Tots.
Cook a little. Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain and put on Tater Tots.
Mix the 4 cans of soup and 2 cans of water or milk.
Mix well and pour over hamburger.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir with whisk and cook until thickened.
Add crisped bacon.
Use over lettuce or tender endive.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, taco seasoning and chopped onion together and spread on a serving plate.
Top with finely chopped tomatoes, lettuce and a jar of taco sauce.
Put grated cheese over top and refrigerate.
Serve with corn chips, potato chips, etc.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Combine in skillet the ground beef and onion.
Season with Italian seasoning and brown.
Drain and set aside.
In a separate pan, cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain. Add to noodles the mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese soup and spaghetti sauce (optional: extra can mushrooms).
Mix well.
Add in the ground beef mix and mix well.

title: easy pie crust(makes two 9-inch crusts)
directions: Combine salt and flour.
Add shortening using a pastry blender.
Then add water and roll dough between 2 sheets of waxed paper.

title: fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Beat eggs with seasonings.
Add water and mix. Dip oysters into egg mixture, then into crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes before frying.
Fry in hot deep fat until brown.
Serve at once.

title: chicken special
directions: Arrange broccoli in a buttered baking dish, then layer chicken on top.
Combine the soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and curry.
Spread over chicken.
Mix together the bread crumbs, melted butter and grated cheese.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter stacks
directions: Spread peanut butter between two crackers (like a sandwich). Melt almond bark.
Dip sandwich cracker into melted bark and cool on waxed paper.

title: relish
directions: First grind everything in grinder with medium small fitting. Put all ingredients into earthenware crock.
Sprinkle with a couple handfuls of salt.
Cover and soak overnight.
Drain after 24 hours.
Pack into pint jars and water bath process about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 pints.

title: bibinka
directions: Melt butter and combine all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: grilled cheese supreme
directions: Butter one side of each slice of bread.
Place 2 slices, buttered side down, on a heated griddle.
On each slice, add Swiss cheese, fresh spinach, tomato and guacamole or sour cream.
Top with remaining slice of cheese and bread with buttered side up. After 2 to 3 minutes, turn sandwich to toast both sides.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
You may have 1/4 of pie a day!

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Feeds many.

title: fresh tomato sauce
directions: Quarter tomatoes and season.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of oil and herbs, mixed, over tomatoes.
Bake at 425° for an hour. Remove skins; mash and add remaining oil.
Toss over spaghetti. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: quick brownies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Stir in milk and remove from heat.
Stir in salt, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into greased oblong pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm; remove from pan when cool.

title: cherry pie
directions: In saucepan, place 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix. Add cherry juice.
Cook until thick.
Add remaining sugar and cook until glossy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice, almond extract, food coloring and 1 tablespoon butter.
Add cherries and mix gently.
Let cool while making pie crusts.
Pour filling into unbaked crust.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter before covering with top crust or lattice top.
Flute the edges and fit pieces of foil around edge of pie.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy mushroom gravy
directions: Mix together the soup and Lipton mix.
Add 1/2 can of water. Stir and heat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add liquids and eggs.
Mix well. Add chopped pecans.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with pecan halves carefully laid end to end in circles until entire pie top is covered.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in slow oven.
Cool.
This is a very rich pie.
Serve small pieces.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Add sauce and seasoning mix.
Heat well.
Line bottom of
9 x 13-inch pan with 6 tortillas.
Pour meat mixture over them; cover with the other 6 tortillas.
Pour soup and milk on top of last tortillas and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream of cashew soup
directions: Saute onion, celery or green pepper and cumin seed in oil until tender.
Stir in flour and saute briefly.
Add vegetable stock and cook, stirring, until it thickens slightly.
Add milk.

title: strawberry fruit and cream squares
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: white crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine as for pie crust.
Reserve 3/4 cup crumbs.
Add beaten eggs and beat well.
Mix buttermilk and soda together.
Add to other ingredients, along with vanilla and dash of salt.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with reserved crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes with oregano
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes thoroughly.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Place wedges into a medium bowl and cover with cold water, let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain and pat dry with a paper towel.
Place potatoes and oil in a medium bowl and toss to coat evenly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: no boil lasagna
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Add ground turkey and brown, then drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, water and oregano.
Boil, then remove from heat. Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, drained spinach, egg whites, 2 teaspoons vegetable oil and salt.

title: strawberries brulee
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add sour cream and the 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Reserve 1 strawberry for garnish. Halve remaining strawberries and arrange evenly in the bottom of a shallow 8-inch round broilerproof dish.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over berries.
Sieve the 1/4 cup brown sugar evenly over cream cheese mixture.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until sugar turns golden brown.
Slice reserved berry; arrange atop dessert.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: boneless pork loin roast
directions: Mix salt, pepper, thyme and rosemary.
Roll roast in mixture; place in glass dish.
Pour sauce over toast.
Cover with Saran Wrap (fold back one corner).
Cook in microwave for 5 minutes on High, then for 20 minutes on Medium.
Turn and re-cover.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes on Medium.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and beat well. Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to creamed mixture until well mixed.
Stir in 4 cups of diced apples and nuts; mix well. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until done.

title: gingered iced tea
directions: Grate the ginger.
Brew it as you would regular tea in about 1 quart of water for 20 to 30 minutes.
To brewed mixture, add the lemon juice and honey to sweeten to taste.
Water may also be added if brew is too strong.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat in honey.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and beat only until smooth (if butter flavoring is used, add to milk).
Stir in nuts and fruits.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold it.
Pour into loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch), lined with wax paper.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for one hour, or until done.
Cool cake in the pan for 5 minutes, then turn cake out on a rack and gently peel off paper.
Turn cake right side up to cool.
Serve plain or frosted.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: In large bowl sift together dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix until blended, but do not beat.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 80 minutes until cake tests done.
(Cake will crack on top slightly.)
Cool on wire rack and then remove and serve with powdered sugar or plain.
Cake will stay moist and fresh if wrapped and refrigerated.

title: angel hair pasta alfredo with crab
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions. Heat sauce and crabmeat in medium saucepan until hot; add pasta, heat through. Top with cheese.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening; add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add flour, milk and baking powder; beat well.
Cook in layers.

title: tudie's salad
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together.
Sprinkle the dry jello powder over the top.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: early-riser oven omelet
directions: In a bowl, beat the egg whites, eggs, milk, seasoned salt and pepper. Pour into a 10-inch ovenproof skillet coated with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle with the ham, broccoli, cheese, tomatoes and onion. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until eggs are almost set. Broil 4 to 6-inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until the eggs are set and top lightly browned. Yield: 6 servings.

title: cookie sheet chocolate cake
directions: Bring the water, cocoa and oleo to a boil.
Pour over the flour and sugar; mix.
Combine the remaining ingredients; add to first mixture.
Bake in greased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.
Make frosting while cake is baking.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Arrange in buttered casserole dish.
Place 1 tablespoon of dry rice on each pork chop, then slice of onion, green pepper and tomato.
Pour bouillon over all. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover; bake about 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: dill franks
directions: Slice hot dogs crosswise.
Combine in small bowl the mustard, mayonnaise and horseradish.
Mix ingredients to taste.
Spread on bottom slice of hot dog and add a thin slice of crosswise cut dill pickle. Cover with the top slice of the hot dog and secure with toothpicks.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: nutty baklava
directions: Butter 9 x 11-inch pan.
Place sheets of pastry one at a time, buttering each until you do ten.
Toss nuts, brown sugar and coconut together.
Cover pastry with 1/2 mixture.
Repeat with ten more sheets (one at a time, buttering each one).
Add remaining nut mixture.
Add 10 more sheets (with butter).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bayou yams and turkey casserole
directions: Turn yams into greased 1-quart casserole. Top with sliced turkey. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend marshmallow cream and lemon juice. Pour over turkey. Cover and bake in moderate oven at 375° for 25 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: rila monastery bean soup(bulgaria)
directions: Soak beans in cold water for 3-4 hours.
Drain and pour over fresh water.
Boil together in a pot the oil, carrots, onion and celery.
When beans turn tender, add sliced chiles, tomatoes, and mint, salt and boil for another 15-20 minutes.
Serve with fine chopped parsley.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemonade together.
Mix well.
Add the Cool Whip and food coloring to the milk and lemonade mixture. Refrigerate.
These can be topped with Cool Whip, if desired. Makes 2 pies.

title: raisin cake
directions: Simmer raisins in water for 15 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix flour and spices.
Cream butter and sugar, beat in eggs, then raisins. Beat until smooth.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased pan.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup, melted butter, chocolate and vanilla; mix thoroughly but do not overbeat.
Sprinkle pecans in shell.
Pour filling mixture over pecans.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and continue to bake until filling is puffed and set about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together.
Roll in small balls.
Dip balls in Chocolate Mixture, leaving top of ball uncoated.
Use toothpick to dip in chocolate.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Debone chicken.
Arrange in bottom of casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Arrange onion and peas over chicken.

title: salad dressing
directions: Whip with electric mixer until creamy. Stir in 1 tsp. celery seed. Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.
On greens, the salad will keep in the refrigerator for several days, it need not be thrown away.
Makes 2 cups. Use on lettuce or cabbage.

title: knox blox
directions: In large bowl combine all gelatin.
Add boiling water, all 4 cups.
Stir until dissolved and pour it into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Form a pocket with heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Put potatoes in foil and top with butter and seasoning. Close foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt mary ella's dandy custard(floating island)
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Pour milk in top of double boiler and allow to get hot.
Add a little hot milk to beaten egg mixture; pour into milk gradually and stir constantly.
When spoon is coated with custard, add vanilla to taste.
(This is thin custard though a little thickened.)
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar to each egg white, one at a time while beating.
Pour custard into buttered casserole dish.
Spoon stiff meringue (the beaten whites) on top.
Brown in preheated 350° oven.
This is delicious served warm or cool.

title: frozen ham and cheese biscuits(just like the grocery store's but a whole lot cheaper!)
directions: Bake
biscuits	according
to package directions.
Cool slightly in
pan.
While
biscuits	are cooking, unwrap cheese and fold each slice
into 4 or 6 pieces.
Stack up on a plate. Open each biscuit and
put
a piece of cheese on each half and add ham according
to
how	much
you
like.
Put
halves back together. Put biscuits
in
a
single layer in a pan.
Freeze uncovered for several
hours
until biscuits are very firm or frozen.
Place in freezer bags.
When ready to serve, take out as many as needed and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
It's best not to heat more than 3 at a time.

title: banana frostee
directions: Combine juice, bananas and vanilla in blender and blend until creamy.
Slice cold fruit and quickly blend into banana mixture. Pour into dessert cups and serve immediately.

title: curly chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish. Add graham cracker crumbs. Press into bottom. Empty chocolate chips then add nuts and coconut. Pour the Eagle Brand milk over top. Bake at 350° until browned.

title: peanut butter apricot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix oil and peanut butter and cut flour with fork until mixture becomes grainy.
Mix milk and molasses and add to the batter.
Stir just enough to mix well.
Do not beat.
Fold in chopped apricots.
Fill lightly oiled muffin tins or muffin cups, 2/3 full.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Blend soups and broth.
Add cheese, spaghetti, turkey and mushrooms.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
