Bake in moderate oven (350°) until bubbly and brown, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8
to 10.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil to hard crack stage.
Turn heat down to low and add cinnamon and red food coloring.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and crack.

title: rice creole
directions: Shape beef into small patties and fry.
Remove from pan. Drain pan and saute onion, celery, garlic and basil with sauce. Add tomato paste and pasta.
Mix to blend flavors.
Add meat patties to sauce.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: southern sweet tea
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan. Add tea bags. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Cover and steep for 10 minutes. Remove tea bags. Add sugar, stirring until dissolved. Pour into a 1 gallon pitcher, adding enough water to fill pitcher. Serve over ice with lemon, if desired.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze in muffin cups.

title: mamie's deep dish apple pie
directions: Pare and core apples; cut into eighths.
Place in a deep, greased baking dish.
Combine sugar, brown sugar, nutmeg, lemon rind and orange rind.
Sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter and top with a thin sheet of pastry.
Bake in a hot 425° oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
In skillet, brown ground beef; drain fat and mix spaghetti sauce.

title: monkey paws
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl. Roll each piece in mixture.
Drop into buttered Bundt cake pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture in saucepan.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Boil. Pour over biscuits. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Turn out while hot and serve.

title: snickers bar cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cookie crumbs and butter until well blended.
Press into bottom and about 1-inch up the sides of a 9 1/2 to 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: popeye's favorite spinach dip
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve with veggies, crackers or bread chunks.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: In large saucepan, simmer first five ingredients for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool 10 minutes.
Blend together remaining ingredients and stir into mixture.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; stir.
Add lemon juice and egg yolks.
Set aside.
In a pan, boil water and grated lemon rind. Add butter and pinch of salt.
Add the two together.
Cook until thick.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Prepare pastry.
Sprinkle cheese and shrimp into pie crusts. Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture into pie crusts.
Cook, uncovered, in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 300°.
Cook, uncovered, until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Mix well.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Add slivered almonds, if desired.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Stir until dissolved.
Separately, beat egg and onion.
Add saltines, ground chuck, salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients, reserving half of the tomato sauce mixture.
Shape into loaf.

title: edna's corn bread
directions: Mix; cook at 500° until brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Sprinkle hot potatoes with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Can also add chopped green pepper, celery, or bacon bits if desired.
Salt to taste.

title: spinach hau pia
directions: Place spinach in sieve and press out as much liquid as possible.
Combine spinach, cottage cheese and coconut.
Combine eggs, sour cream, flour and soy sauce in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth; fold into spinach mixture.
Spoon into ungreased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Refrigerate, covered, up to 2 days.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chex party mix
directions: In a small microwave-safe bowl, melt oleo in microwave on High for 30 to 40 seconds.
Add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce to melted oleo.
Mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into large resealable plastic bag.
Pour oleo mixture over cereal mixture inside bag.
Seal bag and shake until pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents into large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Stop and stir every minute.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Makes 4 cups.

title: homemade cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and lightly flour 2 (8-inch) round cake pans. Cream eggs and sugar. Add oil and butter. Add flour slowly. Add vanilla. Beat on high for 2 minutes. Pour in pans. Cook 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan. Turn out.

title: golden sesame cookies
directions: Bake sesame seed in preheated 350° oven on ungreased cookie sheet until golden, about 10 minutes.
Set aside.

title: white bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups of the flour and the yeast.
In a saucepan, heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm and shortening is almost melted; stir constantly.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in remaining flour as you can mix in with a spoon.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes).
Shape into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl; turn once. Cover; let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down; turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half of dough into a loaf by patting and rolling.
Place in two lightly greased loaf pans.
Brush loaves with melted butter.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until nearly double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order. Cook 35 to 45 minutes in 400° to 425° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, white sugar, 1/2 cup oleo, eggs and milk.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/2 cup oleo. Spread on top of casserole. Bake at 300° until done.
Just before casserole is done, add marshmallows on top and let brown lightly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Grind cranberries, orange and sugar together in a food chopper or blender and set aside. When gelatin has partially congealed, add blended cranberries and nuts, mixing thoroughly. Place in mold. Chill.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water in a large mixing bowl.
Add butter, salt and dry custard mix.
Stir until dissolved.
Gradually add flour, mixing well.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface 12 times. Roll out dough on floured surface.
Spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up into a log.
Cut in pieces and put in greased baking pans.
Cover and let rise about 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: sloppy joes mix
directions: Combine tomato sauce, lemon juice, sugar, mustard, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in skillet.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In the meantime, brown meat in skillet and add onion and green pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: pasta and beans
directions: Saute carrot and celery until tender in olive oil.
Add onion. Saute until onion is light in color.
Add garlic and stewed tomatoes.
Stir in 1/2 can of water.
Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Add broth and simmer for 35 minutes until carrots and celery are cooked.
Add cannellini beans and simmer for another 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta; drain.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add everything together, except cream and fat.
Add the cream and fry in the fat.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put everything except oatmeal in saucepan.
Cook until melted. Remove from heat and add oatmeal.
Stir until oatmeal is coated. Drop onto waxed paper with spoon.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt the stick of butter in ovenproof casserole dish.
Put 2 eggs into large mixing bowl and beat.
Add sour cream, melted butter and mix.
Add 1 package of corn muffin mix and mix again. Add corn Niblets and creamed corn, mix and put in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter	square	or
oblong pan.
Dump canned fruit into pan. Spread
yellow
cake mix over fruit.
Sliver butter over cake mix.
Add nuts, if desired.
Do not mix or add anything. Bake
in 325° to 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean or until	sides leave pan and top is golden brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Break up cauliflower and broccoli flowerets into small size pieces.
Chop onion into small pieces.
Slice bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Drain off fat.

title: bourbon wieners
directions: Simmer wieners in mixture for 1-1/2 hours.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well. Sift flour, salt and sugar together. Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add slowly to mixture. Add pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Space about 2-inches apart and bake at 350° about 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Combine cake mix and next 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat vigorously by hand until evenly moistened.
Refrigerate 1 hour until firm.
Sift powdered sugar in small bowl.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Arrange on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes, until tops appear cracked and cookies are set.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add 1 large or 2 small eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine yeast with mixture and add salt.
Put flour into this, adding one cup at a time and mix well.
Set in refrigerator to chill.
Roll out; cut and let rise 1 1/2 hours in a warm place.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: bishop bread
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over 1 1/2 cups dates and cool. Mix brown sugar, shortening and 1 egg.
Stir this into the date and water mixture and mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to date mixture.
Add walnuts, chocolate chips and cherries.
Batter will be very stiff.
Put in regular size loaf pan and let stand 20 minutes before baking about an hour at 350°.
Other nuts may be used but black walnuts give it a very distinctive taste.
Makes a wonderful Christmas treat.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1 inch meat balls.
Shake 4 or 5 meatballs at a time in bag with Shake 'N Bake chicken seasoned coating mix.
Place meat balls in ungreased shallow baking pan. Bake at 450° about 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve on wooden picks.
Makes abut 3 dozen meat balls.

title: punch
directions: Mix together ginger ale, pineapple juice and orange juice in one large container.
Float sherbet scoops.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown the onion in the stick of margarine.
Mix all other ingredients with the lightly browned onion.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
One may want to double this recipe for company. Bake in a 9 x 9-inch dish or a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Boil the water and oats; set aside.
Cream the remaining ingredients.
Mix all; stir into oats.
Stir well.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash sweet potatoes. Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour pie mixture into unbaked pie shells and bake until done, 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: yummy quick sweet treat
directions: Spread each slice of bread with butter and your favorite preserves.
Roll up the slices and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: creamy layered potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Blanch sliced potatoes for 2 minutes; drain well. Place potatoes, onions, butter and cream in a pan. Stir well and cook for about 15 minutes. Transfer to a large, ovenproof dish. Season well and bake for 1 hour, until potatoes are tender.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese and milk together.
Stir constantly.
Then add remaining ingredients. Serve with chips.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add pumpkin; mix well. Add flour, blending well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Combine corn and broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, onion, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Put in 1-quart baking dish. Combine 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon butter; sprinkle over mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: penuche
directions: Lightly butter 9 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Line with foil. Grease with butter.
Mix brown sugar and milk; cook over low heat (use wooden spoon) until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter; cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: chicken-broccoli skillet casserole
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips. Cook in hot margarine until browned. Add broccoli and carrots. Cook until tender and crisp. Stir occasionally. Remove chicken. Stir in soup, milk and pepper. Return chicken to skillet. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 10 minutes. Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff mixture with fork before serving.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add jello, then cool.
Add buttermilk.
Mix, then fold in Cool Whip.
Congeal in 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: melting moments
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and beat well.
Gradually add flour and cornstarch, beating smooth.
Drop mixture by level teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Serve hot with chips.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Peel and remove seeds from melons.
Dice melons and cook with 1 cup of sugar, stirring well, until melons are tender.
Mix together egg yolks, flour, 1/2 cup sugar, margarine and lemon juice.
Add this mixture to melon mixture and cook until thick. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter flavoring.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue. Chill pie.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: joyce's brownies
directions: Mix ingredients
together except Hershey bars.	Bake in brownie pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take from oven and spread Hershey bars on top.

title: johnny mazetti
directions: Brown pork and onions, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Cook noodles as directed.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and heat until cheese (cut in cubes) is melted.
(I put this in the oven, stirring often, until cheese is melted.)
Unused portion can be frozen.

title: stephanie's peach cake
directions: Drain peaches.
Place peaches on the bottom of greased pan or spray with Pam (9 x 13-inches).
Melt butter.
Mix other ingredients and spoon into pan.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Great served warm with ice cream.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: buttered almond sherbet
directions: Stir almonds and fruit into milk.
Whisk in half of soda, pour into churn, fill with remaining soda and freeze.
Best if "ripened" for one or more hours.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into 2 rib pieces.
Arrange in a shallow roasting pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 2 3/4 hours or until fork-tender. Baste meat occasionally with sauce.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: In a bowl combine milk, sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt, nutmeg and flour.
Beat well to blend.
Sprinkle coconut into pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Pour egg mixture over coconut.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: heavenly waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple cubes with sugar and lemon juice.
Add celery and nuts. Fold honey into mayonnaise, then fold yogurt into honey and mayonnaise mixture.

title: apple cheese ball
directions: Microwave cream cheese in glass mixing bowl for 1 to 2 minutes on "7" power until softened.
Core apple and chop into small pieces.
Add chopped apple, onion, salt, pepper and apple juice to cream cheese.
Microwave for 2 to 4 minutes on "5" power.
Add cheese and chill for easier shaping.
Form in ball and roll in nuts and parsley.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli and rice as directed on packages.
Combine all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
This can be made the day before and baked when ready to serve.
Serves 12.

title: quick bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and divide into a 12-cup greased muffin pan.
(Batter will be thin.)
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: tanta greties marble cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Melt chocolate and add boiling water and baking soda to chocolate.
Divide batter in half; add almond extract to chocolate mixture and add to 1/2 batter.
Place batters by alternate spoonfuls to greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Check after 1 hour.
Let cool and remove from pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: cajun corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo until clear.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick and bubbly.
Add corn, rice, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: cheese grits
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican meal
directions: Brown hamburger or sausage. Lay tortillas flat. On each tortilla, place refried beans, meat, picante sauce, Velveeta cheese and jalapenos (if desired). Roll and lay in baking dish. Cover with chili. Top with grated Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Can be served like that or topped with lettuce, tomato and onion.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Crush 1 package Ritz crackers.
Mix with 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Bake in casserole dish in 350° oven approximately 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over top and return to oven until crackers are brown.

title: ham and cabbage skillet
directions: In a skillet, cook ham in oil for 5 minutes or until brown. Remove and set aside.
Add cabbage to drippings.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir to coat cabbage with drippings.
Mix milk and mustard.
Pour over cabbage.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Return ham to skillet and cook 3 to 5 minutes, until ham is heated through.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fry in skillet with a small amount of oil.
Or grill.
Makes 12 fritters.

title: irma dalhart's cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Add buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oats, nuts and raisins or chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 8 minutes.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Melt margarine on low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are syrupy.
Remove from heat; stir in food coloring.
Add corn flakes.
Take a small amount and make into wreath shape.
Dot with red cinnamon candy.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place cukes and onions in 2-quart jar.
Pour liquid and spices over cukes and onions.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 days.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs and beat 2 1/2 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk.
Beat 3 1/2 minutes.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 25 minutes and remove from pan.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Blend well. Add remaining ingredients.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick on a floured board.
Cut with a floured cutter.
Place 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Beat egg whites slightly.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar. Mix well and pour on wax paper.
Roll mix out very thin.
Spread with peanut butter and roll into rolls.
Chill for 20 minutes and cut into pieces.

title: all-in-one casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased baking dish.
Brown beef and onions. Stir in rice.
Place mixture on cabbage.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and water; pour into dish.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May sprinkle with grated cheese before baking, if desired.

title: rumaki
directions: Lay the half slices of bacon out; cut livers into small pieces to fit inside bacon.
Place water chestnut first at the end of bacon, then liver.
Now roll ingredients firmly together.
Put toothpick through ingredients to hold together.
Put in a nonstick pan at 350° and bake for 30 minutes, until liver and bacon are done.

title: aunt stasia's reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, crumbs and sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread melted chocolate over peanut mixture.
Place in refrigerator for 20 minutes, then cut into squares.
Tastes like the real thing!

title: garbanzo bean soup
directions: Cook in crock pot on high 3 to 4 hours or until potatoes are soft.

title: cisco's salsa(makes 3 quarts)
directions: Best when made at least one day ahead.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spanish tortilla
directions: Saut potatoes and onions in oil until tender. Potatoes will take longer to cook so put them in first and let them cook about 10 minutes before adding the onions. Whip eggs in a large bowl, then add potatoes and onions and pour mixture into a nonstick skillet (spray with cooking spray). Cook on one side until eggs become firm. Flip and brown the other side. Then place on a cutting board. Cut into bite-size pieces and serve.

title: picnic macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk and mustard.
Add macaroni, cheese, ham and peas (thawed).
Mix well, cover and chill.
Serves 8.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix together pizza sauce, garlic salt and oregano. Put on top of beef onion mixture.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and any other favorite pizza toppings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat well and add 7-Up and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: official fair cookie recipe
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: white icing
directions: Beat all together until fluffy, then spread over a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: easy chicken frito pie
directions: Mix onion, soup and sauce in pan and heat until bubbly.
Line casserole with Fritos and add a layer of chicken and a layer of cheese.
Alternate the chicken and the cheese and Fritos again. Pour hot soup mix over the layers.
Top with crushed Fritos and cheese; bake in 350° oven until cheese is bubbly.

title: codfish fritters
directions: Soak codfish in water in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days, changing water every half day.
Remove skin, shred codfish, grind if possible.

title: egg-free potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done but not too soft.
Now dice them and the onions and add to the other ingredients.
Add the Miracle Whip last and use as much as you need to obtain the desired consistency.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and mix until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in the vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter in three 9-inch greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool 7 to 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: spinach and fettuccine
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain. Cook thawed and drained spinach, garlic, onion and red pepper in oil about 5 minutes. Stir often.
Dissolve bouillon in water and add to spinach mixture along with basil, hot sauce and cottage cheese. Stir to blend. Toss with pasta.
Add grated Parmesan cheese.

title: easy tuna
directions: Mix tuna and soup.
Top with chips.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: saucy steak skillet
directions: Coat beef pieces with flour; pound into beef.
Brown beef in 10 inch skillet.
Push beef to side.
Saute onion in oil until tender; drain.
Add enough water to reserved potato liquid to measure 1 c.
Mix potato liquid, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, pepper flakes, bouillon, salt, marjoram and pepper into beef and onion.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender (1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours).
Rinse frozen beans under cold water to separate.
Add potatoes and beans to skillet.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: coconut kisses
directions: In medium bowl, using a wooden spoon, mix all the ingredients together until well blended (but do not add all of the milk until you check the consistency).
The mixture should be moist and hold together.
If necessary, add up to 2 extra tablespoons of the condensed milk.
Use a rounded cookie scoop or a tablespoon and your fingers to form 1-inch mounds of the mixture, about 1 1/2 inches high.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients together except bacon.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (no lid).

title: creamy lime salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package lime gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water. Cool slightly, then stir in the evaporated milk.
Chill until mixture is very thick, but not set.
Stir in the crushed pineapple, lemon juice, cream-style cottage cheese, broken nuts, celery and mayonnaise or salad dressing. Pour into an 8-inch square pan or a 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce. Serves 8.

title: broccoli-cauliflower tossed salad
directions: Arrange broccoli and cauliflower in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Transfer vegetables to a large bowl.
Add lettuce and sweet red pepper; toss gently.
Combine chicken broth and remaining ingredients in a small jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously to blend.
Pour over vegetable mixture; toss gently. Serve immediately.

title: mom's baked beans(mom korsgaard)
directions: Pick over carefully a quart of small white beans.
Let them soak overnight in cold water.
In the morning wash and drain in another water.
Put on to boil in plenty of cold water with a piece of soda the size of a bean.
Let them come to a boil and then drain again.
Cover with water once more.
Boil them 15 minutes or until the skin of the beans will crack when taken out and blown upon. Drain the beans again.
Put them into an earthen pot, adding a tablespoon of salt.
Cover with hot water.
Place in the center a pound of salt pork, first scalding it with hot water and scoring the rind across the top (a quarter of an inch apart) to indicate where the slices are to be cut.
Place the pot in the oven and bake 6 hours or longer.

title: beef cubes in wine sauce
directions: Trim all visible fat from meat.
Put meat in large casserole and sprinkle each layer of meat with garlic powder.
Mix soup and wine together with mushrooms and pour over meat.
Mix well. Cover.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours, then add carrots. Cook for 1 more hour.
Serve over noodles.
Serve with crusty bread and salad.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: whiskey sour punch
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Stir well.
Make ice ring with lemonade concentrate (follow directions on can to make lemonade).
Float ice ring.
Garnish with maraschino cherries and orange slices.
Enjoy!

title: cracked chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and brown and white sugar. Add the egg and beat. Sift and add flour, soda, cream of tartar, and salt. Add 1 tsp. vanilla and the chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes. The secret is not to bake them too long.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add egg yolks and stir.
Add water and butter.
Cook over low heat.
Continue stirring until thick.
Turn off heat.
Add lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: rye bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Blend in molasses, honey, 2 tablespoons sugar, shortening, salt and orange rind.
Stir in rye flour and mix until smooth.
Add enough white flour to handle easily.
Place on floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning so all sides will be greased.
Cover with cloth and place in warm, draft free place to rise until double in size (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Return to board and shape into two loaves.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet sprinkled with corn meal.
Cover with warm, damp cloth and let rise about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Makes two loaves.

title: tomato sauce "au fresco"
directions: Heat enough olive oil to cover bottom of large pot.
Saute garlic 1 to 2 minutes.
Add parsley and oregano and saute another 2 minutes.
Then add crushed tomatoes and sauce or diced tomatoes. Add 1/2 to 1 large can of water, as needed.
Bring to boil, then simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until naturally sweet.

title: chili and rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add chili powder and tomato sauce to make a chili mixture to your own good taste.
In a separate saucepan, cook rice.
In a casserole dish, place a layer of the chili mixture, then a layer of the rice.
Sprinkle with chips and lastly, sprinkle on some of the grated cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are gone.
Place in oven and bake until cheese is melted (about 15 minutes).

title: maryland fried chicken
directions: Blend eggs and water together; coat chicken with flour, then dip into egg mixture.
Dip the coated chicken into bread crumbs. Heat 1/4 inch of oil in 12-inch skillet.
Cook chicken in oil over medium heat until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn over once or twice until thickest pieces are done and no longer pink inside.

title: it's dinner
directions: Mix together spinach, eggs, milk, onion, crumbled sausage and Swiss cheese.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and baking powder together. Beat eggs; add oil and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Mix several minutes.
Put into 2 greased but not floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until bread tests done with a toothpick. Let cool in pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: First, boil 1/2 cup of milk and 2 cups of sugar.
Add 5 tablespoons Hershey's cocoa, oatmeal, peanut butter and butter. Add vanilla with spoon, then put in buttered dish as soon as possible.
Cut in squares.

title: no fail banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening.
Blend in sugar; add eggs, one at a time and beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas and liquid, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine onions and squash.
Add salt and let stand for 1 hour. Pour off excess liquid.
Combine celery and mustard seed in large boiler.
Add peppers, sugar, vinegar, onions, squash and turmeric. Bring to a boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars. Chill before serving.

title: pizza pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, brown beef; drain off excess fat.
Stir in pizza sauce; reduce heat and simmer.
Cook pasta; drain pasta and put in bowl.
Combine egg, 1/2 can onions and Parmesan cheese.
Spread pasta mixture in lasagne pan.
Top with beef mixture and desired toppings.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes to heat through.
Top with remaining onions and bake until cheese is hot and bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put the first four ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
Mix the next three ingredients, then pour over vegetables.
Mix all together well and set in refrigerator overnight.
Crumble 8 slices of crisp bacon and sprinkle over the top before serving.

title: spinach in a wok
directions: Toast the pine nuts.
Heat oil in wok.
Saute the garlic.
Add the spinach and cook until wilted.
Just before serving, add the raisins.

title: quick fruit pizza
directions: Combine
in
a saucepan the rice, water (use juice from fruit as	part liquid) and jelly powder.	Cover and let stand for
5 minutes.
Pour
into 8-inch glass pie plate.
Let cool until partially set, then spread over bottom and sides of pan like a pastry shell.
Fill with fruit.
Cover with topping and refrigerate.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving.

title: low-fat fried bread
directions: Heat pan or electric skillet.
Spray both sides of bread with nonfat spray.
Place in skillet and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garlic salt.
Fry until browned.

title: hash browns au gratin
directions: Thaw potatoes.
In large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, salt, pepper, onion and cheese.
In medium mixing bowl, combine 1/2 cup melted butter, sour cream and soup; pour over potato mixture and mix gently.
Pour into a 3-quart buttered casserole.

title: layer lettuce salad
directions: Put broken-up lettuce in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise.
Spread on top as frosting. Top with cheese.
Cover and store in refrigerator 8 to 12 hours.
Garnish with pieces of crisp bacon.

title: best ever pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Mix the rest of ingredients and beat well.
Add to dry ingredients all at once and mix well.
Cook on greased grill or skillet by 1/4 cupfuls.

title: scones
directions: Let rise twice.
Roll and cut.
Pizza cutters make cutting so easy.
Deep fat fry.

title: 9-inch pie crust shells
directions: Bake at 375° for cream pies.
For pies such as pumpkin that have thin batter, cook at 400° for 15 minutes and then reduce heat to 350° to 375°.
Bake approximately 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese dip
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Cut cheese into chunks for easier melting.
Using low heat, add cheese and melt, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and green chilies and blend thoroughly. Let mixture heat to blend flavors, but do not broil.
Serve with chips.

title: custard icing
directions: Cook milk, flour and salt until thick; let cool.
Then cream in the sugar, Crisco and vanilla flavoring, using mixer, until fluffy.
If too thick, add small amount of water.

title: rich sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine dissolved yeast and remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth, about 1 minute.
Dough will be very soft.
Cover with damp cloth. Place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Shape as desired.
Use this rich dough as a basic for all kinds of sweet rolls and coffee cake.

title: chicken with capers and tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix
bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in egg, then in
bread crumbs.
Heat oil in frying pan; brown chicken lightly
and
drain on paper towels.
Place chicken in a covered casserole.
Set aside.

title: three layer sherbet jello
directions: Dissolve jello in two cups boiling water.
Add sherbet and mix.
Add Cool Whip.
Add drained oranges.
Put in clear sided dish and let jell.
When jelled it will separate into 3 different layers.
It's delicious and pretty too!

title: spanish meat stew
directions: Cut beef in small pieces.
Put in a large bowl.
Add garlic salt, vinegar and oil.
Cover.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Next day, pour beef mixture in a large pot with water.
Cook until tender.
Add onions, pepper, sofrito and the tomato sauce.
Cook until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese in top of double boiler; add sausage and cook for 20 minutes or until sausage loses pink color.
Stir in Bisquick until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: spicy sweet wings
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in baking dish. Add chicken, turning to coat.
Marinate 1 hour in refrigerator.
Drain chicken, reserving marinade.
Place chicken on broiler pan rack. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 30 minutes. Turn chicken.
Baste with reserved marinade every 10 minutes.
Broil 6-inches from flame 3 minutes. Turn and broil until sauce looks dry.

title: johnnie's clam chowder
directions: Dice salt pork; cook until crisp.
Remove pork and save.
Add pork drippings, potatoes and chopped onion in deep pot with the boiling water.
Cook until potatoes are tender, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna binge casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add soup and tuna.
Put 1/2 of mixture in casserole.
Cut artichokes in half and make next layer. Sprinkle grated cheese next, then add rest of noodle mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Heat slowly and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: okra creole
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients in heavy skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, or until okra is tender.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and milk. Beat until blended.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well; stir in zucchini by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole. Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap, vent and microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream; add to squash mixture, stirring gently to mix.
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium-high (70% power) 10 to 12 minutes or until heated thoroughly, giving dish a half turn after 6 minutes. Top with crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pizza
directions: Prepare pizza according to directions on box.
Add more shredded cheese and favorite topping.
If desired, can use green half olives to shape the face of a ninja turtle.
Bake.

title: cardamom coffee cake
directions: Combine 2 beaten eggs, milk, 1/2 cup melted oleo and vanilla/butter extracts.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder, cardamom and 1 cup of white sugar.
Mix ingredients thoroughly and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix until crumbly:
2 tablespoons oleo, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup white sugar and cinnamon and nutmeg and pour over batter and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until wood pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Pour crackers in a bowl.
Pour oil over crackers.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over crackers.
Stir well.
Let set, stirring occasionally, until oil is absorbed.
Put into plastic Ziploc bags to store.

title: sauerkraut sausage balls
directions: Pat out any excess moisture from the sauerkraut.
Mix everything together well and form into small balls.
Place on large cake sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion (saute).
Drain.
To this, add remaining ingredients and cook for 30 to 45 minutes until thickened.
Toppings for soup can include tortilla chips, cheese, chopped tomatoes, lettuce and sour cream.

title: cranberry crisp coffee cake
directions: Mix crushed cereal with melted oleo.
Set aside.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat the 1/4 cup oleo, sugar and egg until well blended.
Add milk alternately with flour mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Spread oleo in bottom of 9-inch round cake pan.
Top evenly with cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle with cereal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add flour and eggs.
Beat well; stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour in shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard together.
Arrange sausage, bread and cheese in layers. Repeat layers ending with cheese on top.
Pour liquid mixture over layers and let stand overnight.
This can be frozen.
May be cooked in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two smaller casserole dishes at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuit coffee cake
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Divide into 2 piles.
Melt butter in saucepan; add water and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Place one pile of biscuits into a greased Bundt pan.
Pour 1/2 of the sugar mixture over the top.
Add remaining pile of biscuits and pour remaining sugar on top.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until rich golden brown.
Place a dinner plate on top of Bundt pan and flip over.
Lift off pan and cake should slide out.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients as listed and roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in sugar and flatten with bottom of glass.

title: lindberg pickles
directions: Grind carrots, peppers and onion on medium.
Grind cabbage with a coarse knife.
Add salt; cover with water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain well.
Add sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar.
You may have to add more to cover.
Do not cook.
Put in glass jars.
Keeps very well and is very good.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Shake milk and flour mixture until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool completely.
Combine other ingredients and beat.
Add milk and flour mixture.
Beat until creamy.
Coloring or cocoa may be added.
(Beat with mixer.)

title: fresh tomato salad
directions: Place all ingredients together in a covered container.
Let stand at room temperature several hours.
Refrigerate several hours; shake well and place in serving dish.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add meal, vinegar and vanilla.
Bake in uncooked pie shell.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, melt margarine.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Add broccoli and cook until separated and tender, then add Cheez Whiz.
Stir until completely melted.
Add milk and soup, then add rice and mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water.
Dissolve gelatine in hot chicken broth.
Set aside to cool.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Cover 9 x 13-inch pan bottom with 2/3 crumbs.
Mix eggs, margarine and powdered sugar.
Cover crumbs carefully.
Beat cream and add drained pineapple.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: In a saucepan, stir flour and milk together over low heat until thickened; cool.
Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla. Add cooled flour/milk mixture a little at a time and cream well. Frosting fluffs like whipped cream.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Use 6 or more potatoes that have been cooked with skins on and cooled.
Peel and dice; place in a greased casserole.
Mix shortening, flour and salt; add milk slowly, stirring constantly over medium heat.
When mixture thickens add cheese; continue to stir.
If too thick, add a little milk.
Pour over potatoes. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Trim fat, etc. from meat.
Cut venison into 1 to 1 1/2-inch cubes or slices.
Pack loosely in jar to 1/2 to 1 inch from top. Fill to cover meat with boiling water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt. Place lid on jars snug.
Pressure cook at 10 pounds for 1 hour. Re-tighten lids and cool slowly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix, chill and drop.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, brown first 5 ingredients, stirring frequently.
Place in casserole with chicken broth.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot fat.
Place in casserole dish.
Brown onion in remaining fat.
Add other ingredients; simmer 30 minutes. Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: pink pudding salad
directions: Stir pie filling and condensed milk together.
Drain pineapple and add to first mixture.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into long Pyrex dish.
When set, cut into squares.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into bowl; cut in butter and cheese as for pie crust, using a pastry blender or 2 knives.
Add water and mix well.
Fill cookie press.
Form straws on ungreased cooking sheets.
Cut into desired lengths.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove at once to cooling racks.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: bluefish
directions: Dredge fish sections in flour mixed with salt, pepper and Accent.
Saute in oil approximately 3 minutes each side (skin side first), depending on thickness of fish.
Place cooked fish in oven pan and lightly dot with butter.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour in foil-lined (9 x 5-inch) loaf pan (or Tupperware); cover.
Place in freezer. Freeze at least 6 hours or until firm.

title: braised duck in sauce
directions: Mix the butter, salt, pepper and paprika well together into a paste and rub it over the duck.
Place duck into an open roasting pan about the size of the duck with slices of onion all around and a bit of water added.
Bake for 2 hours or more at 350°.
When cooked, remove the duck to a hot platter and skim the fat from the juices.
This natural sauce is served in a separate bowl and is good with bread dunked in it.

title: pea-pickin' cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in 3 or 4 (9-inch) pans, whichever is preferred.

title: spinach squares(recipe from the club meeting's herbal luncheon)
directions: Thaw, rinse and press all water out of spinach.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add onion and mushrooms, stirring constantly, until onion is limp.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together in a bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rosettes
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt together, then sift flour and cornstarch and pour alternately with milk.
Fry in hot grease.

title: apple pie (ritz cracker pie)(lots of fun)
directions: Bring sugar, water and cream of tartar to a boil.
Add lemon extract.
Add 21 crackers one at a time.
Boil 3 minutes after crackers are in; do not stir.
At once, pour carefully into a pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with butter. Cover with top crust.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Try it for it is fun and tastes and looks just like real apple pie.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Wear rubber gloves when cleaning peppers.
Chop peppers in blender with small amount of cranberry juice.
Cook peppers until soft.
Strain through cheesecloth.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt the margarine in a saucepan.
Add the onion and garlic and cook over low heat for about 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients, except cola beverage, and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cola beverage and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together in order given.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: mmmpossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Place first 5 ingredients in blender and blend 15 seconds.
Add cream cheese and blend 2 minutes.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until center is firm, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Spread topping carefully over cheesecake. Garnish with fruit (optional).

title: hamburger lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onions, salt and pepper.
Drain well.
Add tomato sauce or add your own spices.

title: betty's orange julius drink
directions: Use liquify setting on blender.
Makes blender full.

title: spicy zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; make a well in center of mixture. Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in shredded zucchini.
Add mixture to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans or tube pan.

title: annie's crock pot chicken dinnerhouston, texas
directions: Clean and de-skin the chicken.
Put everything in the crock pot and turn it on.
Leave it all day.
In the evening, make rice and a cucumber and tomato salad.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place
chicken	pieces,
boned	side
up, between waxed paper. Working
from center, lightly beat until approximately 5
x 5-inches.
Peel
off waxed paper.
Place a ham slice and half slice of cheese on each piece of chicken, cutting to fit. Roll meat up
and
tuck	in
sides.
Secure with wooden picks. Coat each roll with
flour;
dip in beaten egg.	Roll in bread crumbs. Fry in
deep
shortening heated to 340° until golden, about 5 minutes.
Remove
picks
and
keep	warm until served. Also good with a cheese sauce poured over.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In a small bowl, stir soup and sour cream together; set aside. In saucepan, melt butter and cook onion and chili powder for a few minutes.
Stir in chicken and about half of the soup mixture.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Melt and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Will serve 6.

title: spinach pie
directions: In a bowl, combine the spinach, onion and Swiss cheese and spread the mixture on the bottom of a well buttered 1 1/4 x 10-inch deep-dish pie plate or souffle dish.
In a food processor, blend flour, salt, soda, and butter until mixture resembles cornmeal. Add eggs, milk, pepper and nutmeg and blend until just combined. Pour mixture over spinach mixture.
Bake in the middle of a preheated 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes until brown and puffed. Let cool 5 minutes before serving.	Serves 6.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put first four ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Pour into baking dish.

title: blueberry swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla until smooth and creamy; add eggs, beat well. Pour into pie shells, dividing evenly between the three. Spoon blueberry sauce over top
of pies; swirl sauce through batter with butter knife. Bake 40 min. or till center is set. Cool to room temperature; refrigerate. Serve with additional sauce, if desired. Yields 18 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix by directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Poke holes in baked cake with fork.
Bring 1 package coconut, milk and sugar to boil.
Pour over cake.
Mix remaining package of coconut with Cool Whip and spread over cake. Refrigerate.
Bake ahead of time, as it is better the next day.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour, add eggs, stir, do not beat.
Add milk, margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake 325 for 1 hour.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix well the cream cheese and seasoned salt.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup walnuts for rolling.
Chill in refrigerator for about 1 hour before serving with crackers.

title: three-fruit drink
directions: *Or use Five Alive for both.

title: almond roca
directions: Combine butter and sugar into medium pan.
Cook over medium heat until reaches 300° or hard crack on candy thermometer.
Take off heat; add your almonds.
Pour onto cookie sheet.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork up into cubes and brown in oil.
Mix together all ingredients, except pork, and bring to a boil.
Add pork and cook 45 minutes or until meat is done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening, sugar, water and vanilla.
Beat in the eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda; gradually
add to creamed mixture and beat until blended. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 7-9 minutes; do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes before removing. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: cheese and grits casserole
directions: Boil water and grits in large pan until thick.
Add margarine, cheese, salt, seasoned salt and Tabasco sauce.
Fold in eggs. Pour into large baking dish; sprinkle with paprika and bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onions (chopped).
Add chilies and chilli. Place in crock-pot.
Add Velveeta cheese and cook for 1 hour on low heat stirring several times.

title: creamy onion soup
directions: Cook onions in 6 tablespoons butter until transparent.
Spoon onions into blender along with 3 cups water.
Process until pureed.
Cook mushrooms in remaining 6 tablespoons butter.
Stir in pureed onion mixture, 3 cups water, bouillon cubes and thyme. Stir until blended.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt the chocolate with 2/3 cup of the cream in a saucepan over low heat or in the top of a double boiler over barely simmering water, stirring until smooth.
Cool to room temperature. With electric mixer, whip the remaining cream, sugar, liquor and espresso powder until almost stiff.
Fold a small amount of whipped cream into the cooled chocolate.
Fold this chocolate mixture back into the remaining cream until smooth.

title: whipped cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar in mixing bowl.
Beat until combined.
Pour pineapple juice into microwave-safe bowl.
Heat on High (100%) power 25 to 30 seconds or until quite warm.
Sprinkle gelatin over warm juice and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Pour gelatin mixture into cream cheese mixture; beat well.
Blend in whipped topping.

title: chicken fajita pizza
directions: Stir-fry chicken for 5 minutes, until brown.
Stir in chili powder, salt and garlic powder.
Add onions and green pepper; stir-fry 1 minute or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Heat oven to 425°.
Press pizza dough into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown.
Spoon chicken mixture over crust; spoon salsa over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional 14 to 18 minutes or until brown.

title: honey mustard potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Fold in potatoes and chill for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Mix and let set for 5 to 10 minutes or mix ahead and keep in refrigerator.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all 7 ingredients except the rice.
Cook rice while simmering tomatoes and spice mixture for 10 minutes.
Stir cooked rice into tomato mixture.
Garnish with green onions and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey on the grill
directions: Heat grill to about 350°. Place turkey in pan with 1/2-inch sides; salt and pepper the whole turkey. Put about 1/8 to 1/4-inch water in pan. Place in grill with cover closed and let the water cook off. Do not open the grill for the first hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook 2 layers and cut to make 4 layers.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining 1 cup warm water and next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick with fork, bake at 375 F for one hour or until done.
Let cool and cut lengthwise, scoop out pulp, set aside.
Chop coarsely, the skins from 3 potatoes and set aside, discard remaining skins.

title: keeping young children busy in the car(child-approved)
directions: Gather all the magnetic-backed toys your kids play with (don't forget those stuck to your refrigerator) or create some of your own by attaching self-stick magnets to the backs of small toys and put them in a plastic bag for the trip.
Once on your way, your child can spell words or create pictures on the cookie sheet or cake pan with the magnets.
An alternative to magnets are vinyl shapes and forms that stick easily to the side car windows and can be removed and stored in a jiffy.
(Do not put on rear windows, as this can obstruct the view of the driver.)

title: super delicious rice pudding from the oyster bay sweet shop
directions: Boil gently rice, water, sugar and salt until water almost all absorbed.
Add milk, lower heat and gently simmer for 1 to 2 hours or until it is as thick as gravy.
Beat egg, cornstarch and vanilla.
Remove rice from heat.
Slowly stir egg mixture into rice.
Pour into semiflat serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Let set at room temperature 1/2 hour or so, then refrigerate.
Add raisins after egg mixture, if desired.

title: friendship brownie mix
directions: Pour the flour into a 1 quart glass jar with a tight-fitting lid.
On top of the flour, layer the brown sugar, salt, sugar, baking powder, cocoa, chocolate chips and nuts, do not mix.
Cover and store in a cool dry place for up to 6 months.

title: fudge
directions: Combine Hershey bar, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme; set aside.
Combine sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, then boil slowly for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over chocolate mixture, stirring until all is melted and is smooth.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: anna's chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into chunks; set aside.
After 1 cup of broth is removed, add enough water to cook noodles as package directs; drain.
In a large bowl mix soups, broth and sour dream.
Add cooked, drained noodles and seasonings.
Fold in chicken pieces.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish (sprinkle tops with paprika) at 350° for 45 minutes or until slightly brown and bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Slice whole jalapenos in halves.
Drain jalapenos and soak in ice water.
Combine and mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, tuna, lemon juice and walnuts. Drain jalapenos. Shine each jalapeno with oil. Fill jalapeno halves with tuna mixture.

title: maude's cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Mix jello and boiling water.
Add cranberries, orange juice, celery and pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm. Serve with cottage cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
I usually double the recipe.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Prepare onions (peel under cold water).
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Heat oil to 375°.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, Ranch dressing mix and Cheddar cheese together; spread over crescent rolls.
Top with vegetables.
Pinch edges of filled crescent rolls together; seal and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
May be served warm or cool.
Leave whole or may be cut into smaller pieces.

title: bean dip
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Enjoy!

title: egg bread for dressing
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add buttermilk, salt and soda; mix well.
Add enough corn meal to be right consistency, not thick but rather thin batter.
Put skillet in oven at 425° with cooking oil until hot.
Pour batter in skillet and cook until done.

title: sugar-free rice pudding
directions: Put 3 cups of milk in saucepan to heat.
Mix pudding mix and egg into the remaining cup of cold milk.
Add to the hot milk on stove.
Add rice and raisins; stir over medium heat until the mixture comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in oleo.
Add mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and simmer (very low heat) for 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: fruit cake
directions: Grease a tube pan.
Sift flour and soda.
Combine eggs, mincemeat, milk, walnuts and fruit.
Fold in dry ingredients; pour into pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours until center springs back and top is golden brown.
Cool; turn out.
Decorate with cherries and walnuts, if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and bisquick well,
add sausage and blend with hands. Shape into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 min. at 350 degrees.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans, cover with water and soak overnight.
Add the 2 quarts water and ham or ham hock.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add all other ingredients and simmer another 30 minutes.

title: mexican hot chocolate
directions: In large saucepan, over low heat, combine cocoa, sugar, cinnamon, salt and 1 c. of milk; mix until smooth. Bring to simmer; add remaining milk, half-and-half and vanilla. Heat thoroughly. Remove from heat; beat until frothy. Serve in cups or mugs. Garnish with whipped cream and cinnamon stick stirrer. Makes 6 (6 oz.) servings.

title: "mike's famous chili"
directions: Prepare meat one day ahead.
Spice roast with chili powder and cumin.
Cook in crock-pot (with enough water to cover meat) overnight (8 or more hours).
Shred cooked beef with fork.
Remove excess fat.
Place prepared beef in large pot.
Cut bacon into squares and fry.
When crisp, remove from grease with slotted spoon and add to beef.
To bacon grease, add onions, peppers and celery. Saute until tender, adding at least 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Drain vegetables and discard grease.
Add vegetables, chili brick, tomatoes and juice, tomato paste, cumin, chili powder, soy sauce, black pepper and garlic to meat mixture.
Stir until well blended and heat.
Add chili beans.
Skim off any fat from top.
Simmer to blend flavors.
Chili is even better if reheated the next day.

title: no fool pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan.	In bowl, combine flour, sugar and about 1/2 of milk to moisten dry ingredients.
Use remaining milk, beat until smooth.	Pour batter into pan.
Place fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: onion casserole
directions: In the butter, saute and glaze onions.
Put in 7 x 11-inch pan.
Mix soup, soy sauce and black pepper.
Pour over onions. Place shredded cheese over top.
Butter bread on both sides and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtles(microwave)
directions: Arrange pecans on a sheet of wax paper with 4 long halves for legs and 1 short half for head of each turtle.
On a buttered plate, arrange 6 caramels evenly around edge.
Microwave at High for 15 to 30 seconds or until caramels are soft but not melted. Keep warm.
Press caramels down firmly over nuts and quickly form into turtle shapes.
Set aside.
In a bowl mix chips and shortening.
Cover and microwave on Medium for 2 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes until chips are soft, stirring well after each minute. Frost turtles with chocolate.
Arrange on wax paper and let set until cool.

title: tangy pineapple chicken
directions: Place chicken in rectangular microwavable dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 inches.
Prepare Pineapple Salsa.
Place 1 cup of the salsa in blender or food processor.
Add pineapple juice.
Cover and blend about 30 seconds, or process, until well blended; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours, turning chicken occasionally. Cover and refrigerate remaining salsa.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons dark cocoa.
Stir in milk, shortening and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a mixture of brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Place on oven rack, then pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth in a large mixing bowl; add whipped topping. Spread 1/3 of the topping mixture on bottom and sides of large bowl or plastic container.
Crumble cake with your fingers and place on top of mixture, following with remaining topping. Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Other fruit pie fillings can be used.

title: fried deer steak
directions: Place tenderized deer steak into bowl and season with lemon pepper and seasoned salt.
Cover meat with Italian dressing and place in refrigerator overnight.
Mix approximately 3 cups milk and 2 eggs in a bowl.
Place meat into batter and let stay 5 minutes.
Place flour on cookie sheet and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add shortening to frying pan until enough to cover meat. Dip meat into flour and place in frying pan.
Fry until golden brown.
For best results, use deep fryer.

title: honey-orange ham glaze
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over ham.
Use orange slices as decorations.

title: berry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell.
Spoon pie filling atop. Chill until set.

title: barb's crab and shrimp dip
directions: Mix with mixer.
Put in bowl or shape into a ball if desired. Cover with chopped walnuts.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix vinegar, water, slightly beaten egg yolks and sugar. Gradually add in flour. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake approximately 35 to 40 minutes. Beat the egg whites until stiff. Add sugar. Beat some more for sugar to dissolve, then spread on pie and brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts in bottom of pan. Arrange 1 dozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package of pudding mix and cinnamon over rolls.
Add 2nd layer of rolls and repeat pudding mix and cinnamon.
Bring brown sugar and butter to a boil and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with more nuts.
Cover and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil the last 10 minutes of baking.
Let stand 5 minutes and invert on plate.

title: toffee
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and boil slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking to 250°, stirring occasionally until a few drops of syrup form a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
When cool, cut into strips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together into a ball.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients on to boil; stir constantly.
When starts to boil, time for 5 minutes.
Take off and add the remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg yolks. Combine flour, salt and baking powder and add alternately with sour cream and soda.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in steeple pan at 275° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake approximately 55 more minutes.

title: shirley's beans(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain and cover with fresh water.
Bring beans to boil; reduce heat.
Add onion, jalapeno, brown sugar, chili powder, salt, red pepper and garlic.
Cook for about 1 hour. While cooking, cut carrots into very small bite size pieces.
Cook for 30 minutes more.
Remove garlic toes and serve over steamed rice.
I also add 1 link of Healthy Choice smoked sausage (chopped) when I add the carrots.
Makes a very healthy, tasty meal.

title: pink pudding salad
directions: Bring water, pineapple, and sugar to boil. Add softened cream cheese and jello. Mix well. Beat cold milk until fluffy and then add to pineapple mixture. Stir until mixed thoroughly and then refrigerate. You can use other flavors of jello to suit your family's taste. Lime is especially good.

title: fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix with pineapple chunks (not drained) and vanilla pudding.
Chop in bananas.
Chill and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes for 45 minutes.
Dice potatoes.
Place them in a large bowl.
Add salt to taste, pepper, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Marinate 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: country king chicken
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add soups and tomatoes and heat.
Layer tacos, chicken, cheese and sauce.
Make 2 layers in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly all over.

title: lemon-lime jello supreme
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box. Strain pineapple and save juice. Mix pineapple with Jell-O and let gel. Beat cream cheese until smooth; add Cool Whip and blend well. In saucepan, mix pineapple juice, beaten egg yolk, sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt. Cook over low heat until slightly thickened. Put to the side. Apply cream cheese mixture to the top of Jell-O mixture smoothly. Spoon pineapple mixture on evenly and top with chopped pecans.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Mix soup and rice in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
In skillet, brown pork chops; season to taste.
Put pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Put in preheated oven set at 350° and cook for 1 hour. Serve and enjoy.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients and cook together.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Pour into hot, prepared jars and seal.

title: sour cream mold
directions: Place Jell-O in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Add sour cream and continue to stir until sour cream is folded in well.
Mix in pineapple (juice and all). Stir in cut up cherries.
Add nuts.
Pour into mold.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Gradually add sugar to eggs.
Fold in gently coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. (Turn oven on early.)
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt.
Shape into balls (about 1/2-inch).
Place in baking pan; broil until brown.
Turn once; spoon off grease.

title: your own seasoning powder(no salt)
directions: Mix well.
Store in tightly covered jar and keep in cool place.
Makes about 1 ounce.

title: microwave chicken casserole(frances' recipe)
directions: Place noodles, broccoli and chicken in large casserole.
In a medium bowl, combine soup and milk and mix well.
Pour soup mixture over casserole and mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir after 3 and 6 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add orange juice and beat until smooth.
Then add chopped nuts and vanilla wafer crumbs.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly combine all ingredients and put into greased muffin pans. Bake for about 20 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies. Set aside 1/2 cup crumbs.
Add 1/2 cup oleo to remaining cookie crumbs.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: grandma's pickles
directions: Heat until dissolved.
Pour over pickles.
You may not need this much liquid.

title: sweet southern chicken
directions: Melt oleo in pan. Add ketchup, mustard and brown sugar. Simmer a little while until sugar melts. Keep stirring.
Pour over chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or as long as you'd like; the longer it cooks, the better it is.
Bake, uncovered, the last 15 minutes.

title: baked potato topping
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and serve with baked potatoes.

title: wassail
directions: In large saucepan, heat cider and 1 cinnamon stick to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover; stir in remaining ingredients (except orange and cinnamon sticks).
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve in punch bowl.
Float orange slices in punch.
Use cinnamon sticks as individual stir sticks.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl except for nuts; mix well on low set beater.
Fold in nuts and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and ice with cream cheese icing if desired.

title: grape salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with mayonnaise, then beat in pineapple juice.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and grapes.
Add whipped cream.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: corny bread bites
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a mixing bowl, combine cornbread mix and creamed corn.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill mini muffin pans 1/2 full with batter.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, sugar, eggs, soda and salt.
Add pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Put flour in bowl.
Cut shortening into flour real fine.
Add milk until flour is doughy.
Mix until all clings together in ball, handling lightly as possible.
Roll out; cut into biscuits. Put bacon grease in biscuit pan and grease both sides of biscuits. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix first six ingredients and shape into balls.
Roll each ball in a cabbage leaf and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: apple yam delight
directions: Mix oats, flour and brown sugar together.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Mix applesauce and cinnamon together.
In baking dish, layer applesauce, 1/2 dry mixture, yams and 1/2 dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: divinity
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Cook over medium heat to 260° (hard ball stage), without stirring (mixture should boil gently over entire surface).
As temperature nears 250°, beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Gradually pour hot syrup in a thin stream over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed of electric mixer.
Add vanilla; beat for 4 to 5 minutes more or until mixture holds its shape.
Drop
from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Work fast.
Makes about 3 dozen pieces.

title: reuben casserole(serves 100)
directions: Toss bread cubes and melted butter.
Press into 2 (2-inches deep) sheet pans.
Saute sauerkraut in butter.
Place over bread. Layer corned beef over sauerkraut.
Drizzle dressing over meat. Top with Swiss cheese. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: giant creme puff
directions: Bring to boil margarine and water.
After bringing to boil, stir into pan the flour.
Stir until it clears sides of pan.
Dump mixture into a mixing bowl and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread on a greased 12 x 18-inch pan and bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix pudding as directed.
Add cream cheese.
Spread pudding mixture on top of cooled crust when ready to serve.
Top with Cool Whip; drizzle with syrup right before you are ready to eat.
This recipe can use fat-free cream cheese and light Cool Whip to cut fat grams.
This is a really light dessert!

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add egg, sugar and Crisco. Stir in flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in greased pan. Bake at 400° until slightly browned.

title: refrigerated mashed potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, 2 tablespoons butter and seasonings in large bowl.
Stor covered in refrigerator for 2 weeks or less.
Place desired amount of potatoes in greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 cups.

title: mom's remarkable fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (236°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients. Beat until chocolate is melted, blended.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score, cool and cut in squares.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Mix cherry pie filling with almond extract; spread into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread dry cake mix over all.
Drizzle melted butter over top (do not try to completely cover), then sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: rice and chickpeas
directions: Heat olive oil in large saucepan or pot.
Saute onion, tomato and parsley for 10 minutes.
Season.
Add rice and chickpeas with liquid.
Bring to a boil; add broth, cover and simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: puppy chow(a people snack)
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in large bowl in microwave.
Add cereal and mix well.
Cool 1 hour.
Put 2 cups powdered sugar in brown paper bag.
Add other ingredients. Shake until separated and coated.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto baking sheet; do not grease. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Mix oleo and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from baking sheet.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and peel the shell off.
Cut egg in half and take out the middle and fill with ingredients.

title: steak with onion gravy
directions: Add onion to oil in frypan.
When light brown, add meat, water and salt.
Cook slowly for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs. Add hot water, vanilla, salt, soda and flour; beat well.
Add oatmeal and beat.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
(One-half cup of coconut may be added for extra crunch.) Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 55 to 60 (2-inch) cookies.

title: friendship cake
directions: Note:
Do not store in refrigerator while working.

title: sliced pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion fine and sprinkle with salt and let them stand for 2 hours.
Boil all ingredients together and seal in jars.

title: quick cherry cake
directions: Mix all together well.
Put in a greased 11 x 8-inch pan and add a large jar of Musselman's cherries.
Cover over the entire top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes or so.
Serve in squares, plain or with a topping.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Drain, reserving 1 cup of liquid. Dissolve cornstarch in this liquid. Add this back to potatoes. Tear bacon into small pieces. Add remaining ingredients. Remove from stove. Do not cook after all ingredients have been added.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all together; stir well.
