Finish filling can with sweet milk to 3-inches from top.

title: b l t dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let sit several hours or overnight. Serve with Fritos or your favorite chip.
Enjoy!

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut raw meat into thin strips.
Marinate meat one hour only in Dale's, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven on warm before 1 hour marinating time is up.
Place strips of meat on baking sheet. Pepper both sides lightly.
Cook overnight (10 to 12 hours) in warm oven to desired chewy or crunchy stage.
Do not drain Dale's steak sauce off meat before cooking.
Meat will cook dry.

title: dump pudding
directions: Butter bottom of cake pan.
Add pie filling.
Next crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Add dry cake mix.
Put chips of butter and pecans.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions; cut them into inch thick slices.
Mix flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine milk and egg and add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Dip onion into batter and fry until brown at 375°.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle on salt.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill and serve.

title: stuffed pork roast(with onion gravy)
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and garlic into small pieces.
Combine in small bowl with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle with Tony's seasoning.
Generously season roast with Tony's.
Cut several slits in roast and stuff some of onion mixture in slits.
Save remaining onion mixture.
Heat vegetable oil in black iron or stainless steel deep roasting pot (just a little bigger than roast) on medium-high.
Brown roast in oil.
Important:
keep turning roast until all sides are nearly black or appear to have black crust.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add onion mixture and saute until soft and clear.
Cover roast with water and simmer until tender.
Gravy will be dark, thin and delicious.

title: potato soup
directions: In deep pot brown bacon, take out bacon when brown; set aside. Chop onions, cook until tender.
Chop potatoes into small pieces, put into pot with onions, then add milk and bacon.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Simmer on low heat.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 4-quart saucepan; let heat to boil and cook 20 minutes (within 5 minutes, skim off foam on top). Cool and put in containers.
Freeze.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: texas squash
directions: Cook sliced squash for 5 minutes in salted water to cover. Drain and use spoon to coarsely mash squash; do not overmash.
Add remaining ingredients to squash and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake in preheated 325° oven 30 minutes or until well heated throughout.

title: peanut butter-maple cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press with a fork, making crisscross design.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening, 3/4 c. sugar and brown sugar.
Beat in
1 egg and 1 1/2 tsp. vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Set aside one third of the mixture for topping.
Press remaining dough in a greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 8 minutes.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese and 3/4 c. sugar until smooth.
Add 2 eggs and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon over crust.
Drop spoonfuls of topping over filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, cut into bars and store in refrigerator.

title: egg pasta dough
directions: Break eggs into the center of 2 cups of flour.
Add water; with wire whisk beat until very smooth.
Add approximately 2 more cups of flour and work with your hands into a soft dough.
If the dough seems sticky, add more flour.
Turn dough onto a kneading surface and knead for at least 10 minutes.
Put the dough back into the bowl; cover and let rest for 30 minutes.
Roll the dough into desired thickness and shapes to make lasagna, fettuccine, etc., or use a pasta machine.
Serves 2.

title: crab soup
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat just to boiling.
Serves 6.

title: snowy day s'mores
directions: Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Spread them with a layer of fudge.
Cover the fudge with a layer of miniature marshmallows.
Bake in a preheated oven or toaster oven at 350° for about 5 minutes or until marshmallows are golden brown.
Serve with hot chocolate after building a snowman on a cold, wintery day.

title: oriental-style chicken thighs
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix well the honey, soy sauce, catsup, oil, garlic and ginger; pour over chicken and bake in preheated 400° oven, basting occasionally.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes, or until chicken is tender and the sauce is caramelized.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together. Layer all ingredients on a large platter or tray in order given. Cover and refrigerate. Serve with plain tortilla chips.

title: one bowl macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix coconut, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheets, pressing down ends of coconut with back of spoon.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, salt, soda, buttermilk, extract and lemon rind.
Add flour, one cup at a time; beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan 1 hour at 350°.
Cool on rack 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Roll into a ball or log.
Then roll in pecans.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Stir constantly over medium heat.
Bring to a boil for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper until hardened.

title: mexican supper
directions: Fry the hamburger with the onion and chili powder; drain. Salt and pepper.
Heat the beans; add the chilies.
Make 1 bowl lettuce and tomato salad.
Shred the Cheddar cheese into a bowl. Heat the tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and taco sauce mix. Add a dash of salt and pepper.

title: carrots vichy
directions: Place carrots in boiling water with sugar and salt.
Cover the pot with tight cover and cook until water evaporates.
Brown carrots in butter.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: hot ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat in 350° oven until heated throughout and cheese is melted.
Serve immediately so ingredients stay crisp and crunchy.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Combine brown sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Stir in rhubarb, walnuts and black walnut flavoring.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to the beaten mixture.
Spoon into muffin tins which have been greased.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: prehistoric pudding
directions: Note:
Need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) paper or plastic cups and prehistoric decorations.

title: mini italian meat loaves
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving 1/3 cup liquid. In a large bowl, combine reserved tomato liquid with remaining ingredients, except cheese.
On baking sheet, shape into 6 (1-inch thick) patties. Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: vienna tarts
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add the flour and knead until smooth.
Wrap and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick and cut into 2-inch squares. Place 1/4 teaspoon jam on each and fold diagonally.
Press down around edges and place on cookie sheets in crescent shape.
Beat together egg yolk and milk.
Brush glaze onto cookie and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium sized bowl and mix well. Drop by tablespoon onto a hot, oiled griddle.

title: betty's monkey rolls
directions: Spray a tube pan with Crisco. Cut each biscuit in three then layer them in the prepared tube pan. Combine other ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour over biscuits and bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crowd pleasing vegetable bake
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Cut up any large pieces.
Combine cream-style corn, drained whole corn, cheese and soup.
Fold in cooked vegetables and mushrooms.
Turn mix into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Toss bread with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: strawberry-french toast sandwiches
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese on each of 6 bread slices; spread 1 1/2 teaspoons jam over cream cheese.
Top with remaining slices of bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; strain off water.
Mix all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with Durkee fried onions or Cheese Nips crackers.

title: baja lasagna
directions: Saute the following:
chopped onions, mushrooms and chili powder.
Add the cans of diced tomatoes, pinto beans and green chilies.
Spray pan with Pam.
Layer the mixture with corn tortillas, sour cream and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake until nice and bubbly at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, and sugar. Cut in half of the shortening until mixture looks like coarse crumbs. Cut in remaining half of shortening until mixture is uniform, working quickly. Sprinkle ice water, about 1 tablespoon at a time, over dry portion of mixture. Stir quickly to moisten, push to side of bowl, sprinkle more ice water on another dry portion of mixture. Continue until all is moistened, adding water a few drops at a time if necessary just until mixture holds together in a ball. Divide dough in half, roll out half on floured surface until about 1/8 inch thick. Fit loosely into 9 inch pie dish.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Put in 9 x 13-inch or jelly roll pan lined with wax paper.
Mark before refrigerating.
Makes about 2 pounds of fudge.

title: honey bun cake
directions: *Substitute egg whites for eggs and applesauce for 1/4 oil to make low calorie.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Chop vegetables.
Place vegetables in wok, along with 2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Cook until vegetables are almost done. Add chicken.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve with soy sauce and chow mein noodles.

title: pet milk, pineapple salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Stir in jello while still hot; set aside until jelled.
Soften cream cheese with small amount of milk.
Whip combination together.
Add nuts and chill in mold.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Add baking soda, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk to yeast.
Mix with other ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.
Use as needed.

title: mother's dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water. Combine in mixing bowl the cottage cheese, sugar, onions, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to make a stiff dough, beating well after each addition and cover.
Let rise until double in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir down dough.
Put into well-greased 8-inch round casserole (2-quart) or large loaf pan. Let rise (30 to 40 minutes).
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
Turn out of dish. Brush with soft oleo and sprinkle with salt.

title: holiday bread
directions: Add yeast to warm water and sugar in small bowl and set aside. Scald milk and pour into large mixing bowl. Add slices of butter and stir (to melt). Add eggs and sugar.
Stir in well, allowing mixture to cool. Add ground/chopped candied fruit, nuts and spices.
Add flour as needed. Set dough aside to rise. Cover lightly.
Grease pans for loaves or cookie sheets for braids and wreaths.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces and place in baking dish.
Mix soups and wine; pour over chicken.
Cook at 325° for 2 1/2 hours. Add grapes the last 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or bamboo shoots.

title: fish florentine (microwave)
directions: Microwave spinach in package for 5 to 6 minutes on High. Arrange in 1-quart dish.
Layer with mushrooms, then fish in a bowl.
Combine milk, flour, salt, tarragon, mixing well.
Add butter.

title: ham-cheese sandwich puff
directions: Combine ham and cheese; add mayo and mustard.
Spread 6 slices of toast with filling (filling will be very thick).
Cover 6 sandwiches with 6 remaining slices of toast.
Cut each diagonally into quarters.
Stand, crust-side down, in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over sandwiches.
Cover and chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 35 minutes, or until custard sets.
To serve, cut between sandwiches and lift out with cake knife.
Serves 8.

title: cube steaks
directions: Sear the cube steaks in a frying pan. Do not cook thoroughly. Mix the ingredients in a bowl and pour over the meat. Cook over a low heat while turning the meat to finish cooking and sauce thickens.

title: hominy and cauliflower salad (original)
directions: Mix with mayonnaise or salad dressing of your choice.

title: biscotti(italian cookies)
directions: First, combine flour and sugar to form a well.
Second, break eggs into the middle of the well.
Add baking powder and mix with your hands, gradually incorporating all the dry ingredients with the eggs.
Then add shortening and vanilla, continuing to combine dry ingredients with the wet ones.
Knead dough thoroughly until smooth and elastic.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease and flour cookie sheets.
Roll dough into a 1-inch ball with or without filling or roll into a straight stick shape.
Leave straight and cut to size desired or twist into a wreath shape.
If desired, before placing in pan, roll each biscotta in damp sesame seeds to lightly cover the cookie.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Allow to cool.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers. Remove seeds and cut in chunks.
Cover with boiling water.
Cook until transparent (about 15 minutes). Drain.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon salt into a large skillet.
Turn the heat to medium and add the meat, onions and garlic.
Cook until meat is brown but still soft.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, water and vinegar.
As mixture begins to boil; add the rest of the salt, the remaining spices and herbs, the honey and chocolate.
Cover and simmer on very low heat for about 1 hour, stirring and tasting occasionally, adding tomato juice if it is getting too dry.
It should be a thick sauce.
Discard bay leaf.

title: cheese spread appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on crackers or as a sandwich spread.

title: liver and onions
directions: Cut liver in strips; salt and pepper to taste.
Heat oil and add sliced onions; saute until golden brown.
Add liver; stir well and cover.
Let cook three minutes; turn slices and cook three minutes more.
Sprinkle vinegar and cook 3 minutes more.
Serve very hot.

title: "philly" miracle whip wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place a drinking glass in center of plate.
Drop round tablespoon of mixture to form ring around glass.
Just touching outer edge, smooth with spatula.
Remove glass.
Garnish with chopped parsley before serving.
Chill.

title: olive puffs
directions: Mix well.
Wrap small pieces of mixture around green olives. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley flakes, seasonings and bouillon.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended.
Add flour mixture to hot vegetables.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
You can also add ham to this soup if you would like.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let set 20 minutes before serving.

title: roasted-pecan butter pecan pie
directions: Process the roasted pecans in a food processor until they become a relatively smooth butter, 2 to 3 minutes, scraping sides down as needed with a rubber spatula.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, pepper and cubes.
Drain.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add the cheese; simmer until it's thick. Boil spaghetti.
Drain.
Serve with sauce.
Add a salad and garlic bread.

title: mushrooms in wine
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until liquid is reduced somewhat.
Serve warm as an appetizer or veggie side dish.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Combine sour cream, vinegar, sugar and dill weed.
Add cucumbers and top with thin sliced onion.
It is best made one day ahead.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and vinegar in a buttered 4-cup measure. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 12 to 15 minutes or until candy forms a firm ball in cold water or 240° on candy thermometer.

title: fish stew
directions: Use about 1 1/2 or 2 pounds fish filets (no bones), skinned and cut in pieces about 1 1/2-inch square.
Set aside.
Use a stew pot sized with the amount of stew to be cooked, be sure there is a cover for the pot.

title: peaches cream
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in margarine and add milk; knead and divide in fourths.
Cut 3-inch rounds on ungreased sheet and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Blenderize last 3 ingredients. Split round in half and spread with peach mixture.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Add preserves and butter.
Cook and stir to glaze.
Toss with parsley.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions; drain well. Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Slowly add milk and water.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Arrange half of asparagus in buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Place half of eggs, cheese and sauce over asparagus.
Repeat layers.
Combine butter and bread cubes; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown all ingredients together until tender.
Place mixture into mushroom caps.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until mushrooms are tender.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry relish
directions: In a Cuisinart or food processor, combine cranberries, oranges, apples and pecans. After finely chopped in food processor, add sugar and mix well. Leave in the refrigerator for flavors to emulsify overnight.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: Butter a 9-inch spring pan and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Cream the cream cheese, egg yolks, vanilla and white sugar.
Beat until stiff the egg yolks and gradually add 3/4 cup white sugar.
Fold two mixtures together.
Put in spring pan. Bake for 40 minutes at 340°, then pull out of oven.
Top with 1 cup sour cream with 3 tablespoons sugar mixed in.
The sour cream mixture can set out when cheese cake is baking to warm up so it isn't so cold when you put on hot cheese cake.

Bake the cheese cake at 450° for just 5 minutes, then turn oven off and jar door of oven open and let cheese cake in oven to cool at least 1 hour. Cheese cake should be refrigerated and will keep good for at least 1 week in refrigerator.
Top with strawberries, raspberries, blueberries, etc.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: With electric mixer, beat butter and peanut butter. Gradually add icing sugar.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Soften 1 cup of butter and cream cheese. Blend in flour and 1/2 tsp. salt and form a large ball. Chill pastry overnight.

title: chocolate-graham bars
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let cool and cut into squares.
If desired sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen squares.

title: seven day sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cover them with boiling water.
Let stand for 24 hours, then drain.
Repeat this each day for 4 days, using fresh water every time.
On the fifth day, cut cucumbers about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Bring liquid to a boil and pour over the sliced cucumbers.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Repeat on the 6th day.
Heat the same liquid.
On the last day, strain the syrup and heat the liquid again.
Add green or red food coloring, if desired.
Add cucumbers and bring to boiling point.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cover and cook over low heat (stir occasionally) about 30 minutes until crisp-tender.
Serves 4 to 6.
It's delicious.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix
first
three
ingredients together, then roll into ball and
over nuts.
For best results let cheese set out for an hour.

title: pickled okra
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over jars of packed small okra (jars and okra must be hot).
Add to each jar a pod of hot red pepper and a clove of garlic.
All of this must be very hot in order for the seals to pop close.

title: nut roll
directions: Mix together and moisten with milk.

title: full of bologna casserole
directions: Mix all together, put into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish; bake at least 1 hour (maybe 1 1/2 hours) at 350°, or until potatoes are tender.

title: mother's caramel sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot altogether under low heat.
Stir until it is dark brown.
(Be careful not to burn).
When dark brown, pour 2 cups boiling water and stir until it becomes a smooth mixture.

title: holiday fruit bars
directions: Roll crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix with salt and baking powder.
Add fruit and nuts.
Beat eggs and sugar; add the 2 mixtures together.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread into a 7 x 11-inch well greased shallow pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes; cut into bars. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
These will keep weeks in a tightly covered can.
I always put a teaspoon of rum flavoring in mix.

title: apple pecan pie
directions: Peel,
core
and
slice
apples
in
a mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, flour and salt with apples.
Mix well. Let stand 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup pecans in bottom of pie shell
and cover with apple mixture.
Mix melted butter, flour, brown
sugar,
cinnamon
and
chopped
pecans.
Mix well; cover apple mixture with this mixture. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Prepare the number of servings of potatoes needed according to package directions. Spread mashed potatoes in 2-quart casserole. Top with sour cream, cheese, bacon and onions. Potatoes may be covered and refrigerated up to 24 hours. Bake, uncovered, at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: cucumber rings
directions: Slice unpeeled cucumbers and onions 1/8-inch thick.
Also slice onions 1/8-inch thick and mix with remaining ingredients and bring to boil (but don't boil).
Pour into jars and seal.

title: chunky pizza soup
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in oil.
Add tomatoes, pepperoni, beef stock and basil.
Heat through for 20 to 30 minutes on a low simmer.
When ready to serve, ladle into bowls, sprinkle with 1/4 cup shredded cheese and heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl with hands.
Chill 1 hour and then form into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 7 dozen. Freezes well.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze before baking.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine oats, flours, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. In another bowl, combine the egg, buttermilk, oil and vanilla; mix well. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Pour batter by 1/4 cupful onto a hot griddle that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray. Turn when bubbles form on top. Cook until second side is golden brown.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Shred beef or ham in food processor.
Mix cream cheese, onion, Accent and Worcestershire sauce well.
Add beef (reserve small amount) and mix well.
Shape into 2 cheese balls and roll in remaining beef to coat.
Wrap in wax paper and aluminum foil and refrigerate.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In a small bowl beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic powder.
Put in a 9 to 10-inch pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over top.
Sprinkle with pepperoni, green onions and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Serves 12.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Prepare mushrooms and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine oil, onion and mushroom stems and cook until onion is tender.
Add salami, Cheez Whiz and catsup and cook until mixture is smooth. Stuff mushroom caps and bake 8 minutes at 425°.

title: dowling park easy cobbler
directions: Melt
oleo
in 2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and milk. Pour
over	melted	oleo;
do not stir.
Put fruit over batter; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salt substitute recipe
directions: Mix all seasonings together and put in salt shaker.

title: after church omelet
directions: Mix eggs together.
Pour into a medium saucepan.
Add lunch meat, cheese and onions.
Pour picante sauce in.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and 1/2 cup water in saucepan and cook, covered, until soft.
Cool.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Chill and add to rhubarb.
Add pineapple, apples and nutmeats.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin bread ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 1/2 minute.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes. Spread in pan.
Bake about 50 minutes.
Test center with wooden pick.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Drizzle with Brown Butter Glaze.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs. Slice bananas over crumbs.
Slice ice cream 1/2-inch thick. Place slices over bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts. Place in freezer until firm.

title: beer rocks
directions: Roll out two biscuits together on floured surface, to form a 5-inch circle. In a skillet, brown the ground beef and drain. Add cabbage, carrots, water, salt, caraway seed and pepper. Cook until the cabbage and carrots are soft. Place about 3 tablespoons of this mixture in the middle of the circles of dough. Fold the dough towards the center to cover the mixture and form a ball. Put the balls, with pinched edges down, on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: date nut candy roll
directions: In a heavy saucepan, boil rapidly the dates, milk or cream and sugar for 20 minutes or until dates are dissolved, stirring frequently to get the dates well mixed.
Cook until mixture reaches soft boil stage.
Remove from fire and add margarine, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Cool.
Beat until mixture is stiff enough to knead as you would a soft dough.
Anchor a clean, damp dish or pastry cloth over a bread board.
Finish kneading to have an easily handled fondant-like mixture.
Roll in long, thin rolls in waxed paper and put into the fridge to harden.
Cut in small pieces for serving.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: While rice is cooking, put broccoli in pan with oleo.
Set to simmer.
When rice is done, measure four cups.
Put Cheez Whiz in rice, then stir in cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix well and put into baking dish.
Spoon mixture over broccoli and with fork, gently fold in (not too much mixing).
Bake until heated through and bubbly.
No salt is needed.
French fried onion rings can be added to top of dish before baking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until it comes to a boil, then cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil 6 cups water with 4 cups sugar.
Let cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Put couple scoops in a glass and cover with 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: monster toast
directions: Pour about 1/2 cup milk into each of 4 small cups or glasses. Add several drops of red, green, yellow and blue food coloring to each cup; make it brightly colored.
Using a small, clean paint brush, "paint" a monster face on slices of bread (white bread works best). Toast bread slices, butter lightly and munch your monster!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar, leaving no lumps.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch deep-dish shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Middle may be slightly shaky.
Do not overcook!

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk together.
Stir in chicken, rice and cheese.
Fold in peas.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Add zucchini or squash; cook 5 to 10 minutes until squash is tender, but not mushy.
Drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash and onion. Combine stuffing and butter together.
In a 12 x 7-inch pan, put half of stuffing mixture, then put squash mixture on top of the stuffing.
Cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: janis' yeast biscuits
directions: Mix the yeast with the warm water; mix in the butter and sugar.
Add the flour.
Add the beaten egg and beat well.
Store in a large, covered bowl in your refrigerator.
Drop by spoonfuls into muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a bowl, toss cooked macaroni and butter.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate a layer of macaroni and a layer of cheese, ending with cheese on top. Whip together milk and egg. Pour over top layer of macaroni and cheese.
Cook in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple ham balls
directions: In a bowl, combine ham, pork, bread crumbs, eggs and pepper and mix well.
Chill.
Form into 10 balls; set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, butter and eggs.
Mix in other ingredients. Batter is real stiff.
Bake in tube pan at 375 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts with pecans
directions: Cut a cross in stem end of each sprout for more even cooking. Cook in boiling water to cover for 5 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
In deep skillet over low heat, stir sugar and butter until sugar dissolves.
Add Brussels sprouts and pecans; toss until well glazed.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese and meat balls(with bran cereal)
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, combine bran cereal, egg, milk and pepper.
Mix well.
Let stand about 5 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add ground beef and cheese, mixing until well combined. Shape into 1-inch meat balls.
Place in single layer in greased, shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove from oven and immediately loosen meat balls from pan.
Serve with Savory Onion Sauce over noodles, if desired. Yield: About 2 1/2 dozen meat balls, 6 servings.
Per serving: (without sauce) 160 calories; 2.3 gr fiber.

title: grilled tuna and swiss
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except bread and margarine; mix well.
To assemble sandwiches, spread 1/2 cup of tuna mixture on each of 5 slices of bread.
Cover with remaining bread slices.
Spread margarine on outside of each sandwich.
Heat large skillet over medium-high heat or heat griddle to 375°.
Add sandwiches; cook 1 to 2 minutes on each side or until bread browns and sandwiches are hot.
Yields 5 sandwiches.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each breast with a slice of bacon.
In bottom of a flat casserole dish, sprinkle a base of chipped beef.
Place chicken on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all.
Bake 3 hours, uncovered, at 275°.
Good served over rice and can be made ahead and refrigerated until cooking time.

title: pole's apple cake
directions: Blend eggs, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add flour, little at a time.
Blend well.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour.
Remove from pan after 30 minutes.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, onion and salt.
Shape mixture into 50 to 60 meatballs.
Combine grape jelly, chili sauce and lemon juice in large skillet.
Heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth.
Add meatballs; simmer 1 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: In 3-quart microwave safe dish, combine oil, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cover with lid; microwave on High 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once during cooking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; cut into bite-size pieces.
Roll Hi Ho crackers into crumbs.
Melt oleo and mix with crumbs.
Put 1/2 of crumbs in 9 x 13-inch dish, then add chicken pieces.
Mix soups, sour cream and water chestnuts; pour over chicken.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato apricot casserole
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon, orange peel and apricot juice.
Bring to a hard boil.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until heated through.

title: joyce cake
directions: Place first ten ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and let cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in large pan.

title: baked scrod
directions: Put a light film of oil in the bottom of a pan.
Place fish; sprinkle onion over fish, then garlic, cheese, bread crumbs and basil.
Sprinkle over with oil lightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until fish flakes.
Do not o°ercook.

title: chocolate fruit balls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls and freeze. Mix chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler until melted.
Keep chocolate warm.
Dip balls.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, cardamon, sugar and salt. Add the milk.
Add the egg yolks and then add the oil.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in mixture.
Bake in hot waffle iron until light golden. Serve hot or like the Norwegians, serve cold with butter and slice of goat cheese on top.
Makes 10 waffles.

title: pineapple raisin drops
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Add beaten egg.
Add raisins and pineapple.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Drop from a teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off of canned fruit saving pineapple and apricot juice.
Mix pudding with saved juice; add canned fruit.
Right before serving, add peeled apple and banana.
Note:
Vanilla instant pudding may be substituted.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Place green beans on bottom. Layer soup, water chestnuts, cheese and onions.
Place another layer beans, then soup on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. When bubbly, layer cheese and onions on top.
Bake until onions brown and cheese melts.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry as package directs. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly, then beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell; bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 300°; bake 30 minutes longer, or until knife inserted one inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Prepare greased cookie sheet pan.
Cook sugar, Karo and water until mixture begins to string like hair off the spoon.
Add peanuts and cook until mixture begins to cover to a light brown. Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt and soda.

title: dill dip
directions: Stir all ingredients and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: tortillas a la maison
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add chicken and vegetables.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in flour tortillas. Put seam side down in lightly buttered dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: bishops chicken wings
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour over chicken wings. Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Drain well.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, until dark and chewy.

title: pecan strudel
directions: Sift flour and measure. Add sugar, salt and cut in butter (as for a pie crust). Add yeast to the 1/4 cup hot water to dissolve, then combine with sour cream and egg yolks and add to first mixture. More flour may be needed to form a soft smooth dough. Place in bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight. Next morning, form into 3 balls. Roll each into a rectangle about 1/4 inch thick. Spread with filling and roll up as a jelly roll. Let rise for one hour. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Ice while warm and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: chicken lo-cal
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups water in pressure pan.
Arrange chicken and onion in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cook for 25 to 35 minutes.
